8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 375 F. Grease two 8 or 9-inch square baking pans and set aside.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca In a large mixing bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups of the flour, yeast, dry milk, and salt. Mix well and set aside.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca In a small saucepan, heat the pineapple juice, 1/2 cup water, shortening, and honey until warmed to about 120 to 130 F. (Shortening does not need to melt.)
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Add the warmed liquid mixture to flour mixture.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Add the 2 eggs. Blend at low speed until moistened, then beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca By hand, gradually stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough. (You might not use all of the flour. Reserve any remaining flour for kneading and shaping the dough.)
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Knead the dough on a floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place for 15 minutes.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Punch down dough. On a lightly floured surface, divide the dough in half and shape it into a ball. Press one ball of dough evenly into each of the prepared baking pans.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Sprinkle the top of the dough lightly with flour. With a knife, cut the dough into 9 rolls in each pan, cutting almost to the bottom of the pan.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Cover and let rise in a warm place for 15 minutes.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Remove from pan. Brush with melted butter. Cool completely on a rack.
8852b39e-6626-436c-977f-688d7a0a6dca Serve and enjoy!
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Gather the ingredients.
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Line rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. Place the pepperoni sticks in a large bowl and microwave until the fat is rendered, about 3 minutes.
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Using tongs, transfer pepperoni to a paper towel–lined plate. Reserve 3 tablespoons of the pepperoni oil.
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Combine water, milk, and sugar in a medium bowl and microwave until temperature registers 110 F, 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in reserved pepperoni oil and yeast and let the yeast bloom for about 5 minutes or until foamy.
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Using a stand mixer fitted with a dough hook, mix flour, and salt on low speed until combined, about 10 seconds. With the mixer running, slowly add yeast mixture until incorporated. Increase speed to medium and mix until dough is shiny and smooth and pulls away from the sides of the bowl, about 8 minutes. If the dough feels wet add more flour 1 tablespoon at a time.
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Transfer dough to a lightly floured counter and divide into 8 equal pieces.
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Working with 1 piece at a time while keeping the remaining pieces covered with plastic so as not to dry out, form dough into balls, cover with plastic, and let rest for 5 minutes. Toss pepperoni wedges with 1 tablespoon flour to coat. Working with 1 dough ball at a time, use your hands to press the ball into a 6 by 4-inch rectangle. Starting along the short side of the rectangle, lay 2 pieces of pepperoni side by side, 1/2 inch apart, and top with 2 tablespoons cheese and roll into a tight cylinder, pinching the ends of the rolls to seal.
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Arrange rolls seam side down on the prepared baking sheet. Cover with plastic and let rise until doubled in size, about 40 minutes. While the rolls rise, preheat the oven to 375 F.
582c0d2d-2bd8-4a4c-9dc8-5fda519cf292 Brush rolls with egg mixture and bake until golden brown, 24 to 28 minutes. Transfer the baking sheet to a wire rack and let cool for at least 15 minutes and serve. Enjoy!
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Prepare the sponge cake: Separate the eggs by placing the yolks and whites into different bowls. Add 1/2 cup sugar to the yolks and 1/2 cup sugar to the whites. Beat the yolks until creamy and beat the whites until stiff peaks form.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Fold the whipped egg whites into the creamy yolk mixture. Gradually add the flour, then mix in the butter.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Pour into a greased 10-inch cake pan. Bake in preheated oven for about 20 minutes, or until spongy and golden.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Remove from oven and allow to cool completely.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Make the pastry cream: In a large saucepan, bring to a boil the butter, milk, and cream.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 As this mixture is cooking, combine the sugar, cornstarch, and eggs in a bowl and whip until ribbons form.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 When the cream, milk, butter mixture reaches the boiling point, gradually whisk in the egg mixture and cook to boiling. Boil for one minute.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Assemble the Boston cream pie: Cut the sponge cake into two layers.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Spread the flavored pastry cream over one layer. Top with the second cake layer. Reserve a small amount of the pastry cream to spread on sides to adhere to almonds.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Place chocolate and water in a microwave-safe bowl and heat in 30-second intervals, stirring each time, until melted. Spread a thin layer of chocolate icing on the top of the cake. If some of the icing drips down the side of the cake, don’t worry. This will be covered up with the almonds.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Combine the white icing ingredients and warm to approximately 105 F. Adjust the consistency with water. The icing should flow freely. Spoon white icing into a pastry bag fitted with a small tip.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 After pouring on the chocolate icing, follow immediately by piping spiral lines of the white icing starting from the center of the cake working your way outwards. Using a wooden skewer, pull the white lines through the chocolate layer to form a decorative web design. Start in the center of the cake and pull outward to the edge.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Spread sides of cake with a thin coating of the reserved pastry cream. Press on the toasted almonds.
e9188840-856a-4d2a-a4d6-9191a2288968 Serve and enjoy!
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Gather your ingredients.
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Add the butter to a medium heavy-bottomed pot. Allow the butter to melt over medium heat and add the chopped carrots, celery, onion, and garlic.
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Add a teaspoon of salt and saute the vegetables on medium heat until they are softened and slightly browned, about 10 minutes.
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Add the chicken broth and thyme to the vegetables and pour it all into a blender and blend until smooth.
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Pour the mixture back into the pot and add the beer. Heat on medium heat, whisking to incorporate the beer.
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Add the half and half and softened cream cheese and gently whisk into the soup. Make sure the cream cheese is softened; it will incorporate into the soup more smoothly this way.
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Toss the shredded cheddar with the cornstarch until the cheese is coated evenly. Add one handful of cheese at a time, whisking it into the soup until it is melted and incorporated. If you add too much at one time, it can become clumpy, so do this slowly. Simmer for another five minutes until it has thickened, stirring frequently.
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Season the soup with more salt as needed and add the pepper. If you want the soup even smoother you can pass it through a sieve or add it back to the blender and blend again.
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Serve the soup in hollowed out pretzel bread bowls or regular bread bowls. You can also serve in a plain old bowl with some delicious bread or pretzel sticks!
ac95e65f-5563-4a63-adef-22d20b1599a2 Top with the chopped chives and bacon.
3075aa41-85a5-4c89-b749-d74ae2bbe12a Gather the ingredients.
3075aa41-85a5-4c89-b749-d74ae2bbe12a Sprinkle the Kosher salt and a few good grinds of black pepper onto your chopping board and spread. Press the chicken thighs, skin-side surface down into the salt and pepper then roll each thigh tight and place in a bowl.
3075aa41-85a5-4c89-b749-d74ae2bbe12a In another small bowl mix the garlic, vinegar, brine, wine and sugar and lightly whisk. Add the olives, prunes and capers, stir, then pour everything over the chicken thighs. Cover the dish tightly with plastic or wax wrap and place into the fridge to marinate overnight.
3075aa41-85a5-4c89-b749-d74ae2bbe12a Preheat the oven to 350 F.
3075aa41-85a5-4c89-b749-d74ae2bbe12a When ready to cook, lift the thighs from the dish and pat dry with kitchen paper. Heat the oil in a frying pan until hot but not smoking.
3075aa41-85a5-4c89-b749-d74ae2bbe12a Add the thighs and sear all over until the thighs are golden brown and slightly crisp on the skin-side surface.
3075aa41-85a5-4c89-b749-d74ae2bbe12a Pack the browned thighs into shallow ovenproof baking then pour over the marinade, olives, prunes and capers. Bake in the center of the preheated oven for 45 minutes basting the chicken with the marinade from time to time. The marinade will reduce, and the chicken will turn dark golden and slightly caramelized.
3075aa41-85a5-4c89-b749-d74ae2bbe12a Serve while piping hot with extra olives and capers on the side and rice, or a mixture of rice and quinoa, or pasta. The Chicken Marbella also works well with creamy mashed potatoes.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Gather the ingredients.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Wrap each hot dog with a slice of bacon so that the entire hot dog is covered in bacon. Secure with a toothpick and place them in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes. This helps the bacon stick to the hot dog and will keep it from falling off when they’re cooked.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Heat the grill or stove on medium heat. Keep the temperature on medium heat so the bacon cooks without burning. Remove the toothpick from the hot dogs.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 While the hot dogs are cooking, prepare the crema.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Whisk together the sour cream, mayonnaise, lime juice, cilantro, salt, and pepper in a small bowl. You can also blend it in the food processor.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Cut a pocket into the center of each of the rolls.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Butter the outside of the rolls and then griddle them on the same grill or pan as the hot dogs.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Kind of pull them apart a bit so the inside of the roll gets a little crisp and cook them cut side down. You can flatten them with a lid if you wish. Cook until they are golden brown and seared.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Warm the beans in the microwave or a small pot until steaming. Spread a few tablespoons of the refried beans into the bottom of each roll.
872a18c4-abbe-4f48-8c70-62789680ef75 Add the hot dog into the roll and then top with diced avocado, tomato, red onion, jalapeño, cilantro, and a drizzle of the cilantro-lime crema. Serve immediately with your favorite sides.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Gather your ingredients.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Chop the sun-dried tomatoes. Toss with the chopped avocado, onion, cilantro, salt, and lime juice in a large bowl.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Turn the egg roll wrappers on an angle, so that the corner is facing you. Place one to two tablespoons of filling towards the center of the wrapper. Brush the edges of the wrapper with water. You can use a pastry brush or your finger.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Fold the corner over the filling tightly.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Start rolling the egg roll in the same direction and fold in the two side corners as you roll. Keep the wrapper tight around the filling.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Continue rolling until the filling is completely enclosed in the wrapper. Set it aside on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Continue filling wrappers until you run out of filling.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Pour oil into a pot to a 2-inch depth and heat to 350 F. Add three or four rolls to the hot oil at a time. Cook for three to four minutes or until golden brown.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Remove the egg rolls from the oil and allow them to drain on a paper towel lined plate.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd While the egg rolls are frying, gather the ingredients for the dipping sauce.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Blend the dipping sauce ingredients together in a blender or food processor.
77b9d0c7-b9b1-47ef-bee0-60c09b2729cd Cut the hot egg rolls on an angle and serve them with the dipping sauce!
7a9c5a72-72b4-4993-867c-4bd0dcc798cb Gather the ingredients.
7a9c5a72-72b4-4993-867c-4bd0dcc798cb Shape the meat into four 6-ounce burgers. Make each patty a little larger than the bun since it will shrink while cooking. Add an indentation in the center of each burger with your thumb. This will prevent swelling in the center as they cook. Sprinkle lightly with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper.
7a9c5a72-72b4-4993-867c-4bd0dcc798cb Heat the unsalted butter in a heavy skillet over medium to medium-low heat. Add one or two burgers to the skillet and cook for about 3 to 4 minutes on each side, waiting until the bottom of the burger releases easily from the pan before flipping.
7a9c5a72-72b4-4993-867c-4bd0dcc798cb Continue to cook the burgers, flipping occasionally, until they register 160 F on an instant-read thermometer. Repeat with the remaining burgers.
7a9c5a72-72b4-4993-867c-4bd0dcc798cb Assemble the burgers in the buns with your choice of sauce and toppings.
7a9c5a72-72b4-4993-867c-4bd0dcc798cb Enjoy your bison burgers!
4dd2ef84-ce2e-4cc5-ad47-490bb6ae10e4 Gather the ingredients.
4dd2ef84-ce2e-4cc5-ad47-490bb6ae10e4 Split each hot dog or sausage lengthwise while keeping the two halves together.
4dd2ef84-ce2e-4cc5-ad47-490bb6ae10e4 Heat a sauté or grill pan on high heat. Add the oil, onions, and salt and sauté or grill for 2 to 3 minutes or until slightly softened and browned. Make sure to do this on high heat to get good golden color and flavor.
4dd2ef84-ce2e-4cc5-ad47-490bb6ae10e4 Remove the onions from the pan and add the hot dogs. Sear for about 2 minutes per side or until heated through and lightly browned or charred. Cover to keep warm while you toast the buns.
4dd2ef84-ce2e-4cc5-ad47-490bb6ae10e4 Remove the dogs from the pan and add the buns. Toast them split-side down. You can open the buns as wide as you want. Toast them until just lightly browned.
4dd2ef84-ce2e-4cc5-ad47-490bb6ae10e4 Add the dogs to the buns and add some grilled onions to the side of the dogs. Add the softened cream cheese to a plastic or piping bag. Cut the bottom off of the bag and squirt the cream cheese over the top of the dog. You can also just slather it into the bun before you add the hot dog. Then top with fresh jalapeno slices, Sriracha, and mustard. You can also add sauerkraut.
4dd2ef84-ce2e-4cc5-ad47-490bb6ae10e4 Serve immediately with your favorite chips or sides.
623601f8-8034-442b-9b5f-a66f8baa4b03 Gather the ingredients.
623601f8-8034-442b-9b5f-a66f8baa4b03 Pour one shot glass full of whiskey and fill a separate shot glass with pickle juice.
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b Gather the ingredients.
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b Heat a charcoal or gas grill to medium-hot (you should be able to hold your hand about an inch over the cooking grate for about 2 seconds)—if the grill is too hot the beets will burn before they cook through. If you need a hotter grill to cook other things, cook the beets on the cooler edges of the grill.
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b While the grill heats, peel and slice the beets.
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b Brush the beets with olive oil or vegetable oil. (Or, put the slices in a large bowl, drizzle with the oil and toss to coat the beets evenly.)
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b Place the beets on the grill and sprinkle lightly with salt, if you like.
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b If using a gas grill, close the cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b Turn the beets over and continue cooking until the beets are tender and grill-marked, another 8 to 10 minutes.
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b Serve the beets hot, warm, or at room temperature. Drizzle them with additional olive oil for serving, if you like. This is also a great time to use any nut oils (toasted walnut oil or hazelnut oil in particular) since they so perfectly complement the earthy-yet-sweet flavor of grilled beets. (That's it. It's really just slicing the beets and setting them on the grill until they're tender!)
7db4bf56-f8b8-48b0-97cd-1a676ff9534b Enjoy!
0b58a1e0-cd7d-4b9d-b9f7-ed18d4e4b230 Pour oil to a depth of 2" in a 6 quart Dutch oven. Heat over medium-high heat until your deep-fry thermometer reads 350°.
0b58a1e0-cd7d-4b9d-b9f7-ed18d4e4b230 Divide mozzarella slices among 4 slices of bread. Season with salt and pepper, and cover with the remaining cheese slices to make 4 sandwiches. Trim the crusts.
0b58a1e0-cd7d-4b9d-b9f7-ed18d4e4b230 Take out 3 bowls and place the flour in one bowl, the eggs (cracked and whisked) in another and the breadcrumbs in the last bowl. Dredge each sandwich in flour, coat in eggs and coat in breadcrumbs before putting on the frying pan.
0b58a1e0-cd7d-4b9d-b9f7-ed18d4e4b230 Fry until golden brown, about 1-2 minutes on each side.
0b58a1e0-cd7d-4b9d-b9f7-ed18d4e4b230 Let each sandwich rest for about a minute after it's been removed from the oil, then spoon some sauce over the top and serve.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 Gather the ingredients.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 Crack the eggs into a glass mixing bowl and beat them until they turn a pale yellow color.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 Add the milk to the eggs and season to taste with salt and white pepper. Whisk the eggs like crazy. If you're not up for that, you can use an electric beater or stand mixer with the whisk attachment. Whatever device you use, you're trying to beat as much air as possible into the eggs. Note that it may be easier and quicker to beat the eggs in two batches (4 at a time) to make sure you don't have any lumps.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 Heat a heavy-bottomed, nonstick sauté pan over medium-low heat. Add the butter and let it melt.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 When the butter in the pan is hot enough to make a drop of water hiss, pour in the eggs. Don't stir. Let the eggs cook for up to a minute or until the bottom starts to set but doesn't brown.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 With a heat-resistant rubber spatula, gently push one edge of the egg into the center while tilting the pan to allow the still liquid egg to flow in underneath. Repeat with the other edges, until there's no liquid left.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 Turn off the heat and continue gently stirring and turning the egg until all the uncooked parts become firm. Don't break up the egg, keeping the curds as large as possible. If you're adding any other ingredients, quickly add them now.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 Transfer to a plate when the eggs are set but still moist and soft. Eggs are delicate, so they'll continue to cook for a few moments after they're on the plate.
2c1b56f0-8039-44d8-baf6-88001eb781c3 Serve immediately and enjoy.
a86d7821-b2d4-4ead-a309-f7de09a00c09 Gather the ingredients.
a86d7821-b2d4-4ead-a309-f7de09a00c09 Rinse the cherries then remove the pits using a cherry pitter or alternative objects such as a toothpick, chopstick, or unbent paper clip. Work over a bowl to catch the cherry juice along with the pits, placing the pitted cherries in a separate bowl.
a86d7821-b2d4-4ead-a309-f7de09a00c09 In a medium saucepan, bring the water to a boil. Add the brown and white sugars and stir until completely dissolved.
a86d7821-b2d4-4ead-a309-f7de09a00c09 Reduce the heat to a simmer. Add the vanilla extract, cardamom, cloves, allspice, star anise, and cinnamon stick. Simmer for about 10 minutes.
a86d7821-b2d4-4ead-a309-f7de09a00c09 Remove the pan from the heat and discard the spices. Stir in the brandy and add the pitted cherries along with any juice. Let cool to room temperature.
a86d7821-b2d4-4ead-a309-f7de09a00c09 Use a slotted spoon to transfer the cherries to a quart jar or two pint jars.
a86d7821-b2d4-4ead-a309-f7de09a00c09 Pour the liquid over the cherries, covering them completely while leaving 1/2-inch of headspace in the jar. Secure the lid.
a86d7821-b2d4-4ead-a309-f7de09a00c09 Place the jar in the refrigerator. If you prefer to use a traditional canning method, process the jar in boiling water for 10 minutes, allow it to cool, then store in a cool, dark place such as a cupboard or pantry. Either way, let the brandied cherries rest for 6 weeks before using to allow the flavor to develop.
d63ca82a-605c-4ba1-8651-78dd363887c2 Gather the ingredients.
d63ca82a-605c-4ba1-8651-78dd363887c2 Place all of the ingredients into a saucepan and bring to a simmer at medium heat. Cook for 5 minutes.
d63ca82a-605c-4ba1-8651-78dd363887c2 Place the ingredients in a blender and blend together being careful of the steam so that it doesn't blow the lid off.
d63ca82a-605c-4ba1-8651-78dd363887c2 Enjoy!
0f139d01-81c3-4e5e-91da-42477e0e1c3b Gather the ingredients.
0f139d01-81c3-4e5e-91da-42477e0e1c3b Prepare a gas or charcoal grill to medium heat: You should be able to hold your hand about an inch above the cooking grate for 3 to 4 seconds before pulling it away from the heat. If you are also using the grill to cook something else that requires more heat, place the peaches around the edges; they're cooler. Or cook dinner, let the fire cool down, and then grill the peaches.
0f139d01-81c3-4e5e-91da-42477e0e1c3b Cut the peaches in half and pit them.
0f139d01-81c3-4e5e-91da-42477e0e1c3b If you want to add cinnamon and/or sugar, grill entire peach halves; otherwise, you can cut them into wedges, if you like. Peeling the peaches isn't necessary for the grill, but if you want to, you can.
0f139d01-81c3-4e5e-91da-42477e0e1c3b Lightly brush the peaches with the oil, being particularly aware of coating the cut sides well.
0f139d01-81c3-4e5e-91da-42477e0e1c3b Set the oiled peaches on the medium hot grill. Make sure they aren't touching so the hot air of the grill can circulate around each piece.
0f139d01-81c3-4e5e-91da-42477e0e1c3b Cook the peaches until grill marks form, turning as necessary to mark all cut sides for the best presentation. Turn the peach halves over, sprinkle with the cinnamon and sugar, if using. Cook until the peaches are tender, but not falling apart, about 8 minutes total.
0f139d01-81c3-4e5e-91da-42477e0e1c3b Serve grilled peaches hot, warm, or even at room temperature. Enjoy!
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 Gather the ingredients.
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 While technically optional, the first step for the best tasting grilled steak is to salt it. Put the salt in a small bowl or ramekin. If using the pepper and/or cayenne, add them to the salt and mix.
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 Liberally sprinkle the skirt steak with sea salt or kosher salt and let it sit for at least 30 minutes at room temperature or up to overnight in the fridge. In any case, bring the meat to about room temperature, or at least let it sit out to take the chill off before cooking it to help ensure even cooking.
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 While the meat sits, make sure the cooking grate on your charcoal or gas grill is cleaned and well-oiled, then heat the grill to high heat. You should be able to hold your hand about an inch over the grill grate for 1 second before it feels too hot. If using a charcoal grill, build the fire to one side so you'll also have a cooler area where you can move the steak(s) if it's seared and browned on the outside but not quite ready to take off the grill completely (if you're using a gas grill you'll be able to turn off a burner if need be).
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 Set the steak(s) on the grill and cook, without moving, until that side is seared and releases from the grill of its own accord, about 3 minutes for medium-rare, 4 minutes for medium.
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 Turn and cook on the other side to the same effect, about 3 to 4 more minutes. You can use a meat thermometer to get an accurate temperature if you like. For rare, remove the steak(s) at 120 F to 125 F; medium-rare 125 F to 130 F; and medium 130 F to 135 F.
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 Remove the steak(s) from the grill, cover loosely with foil, and let sit at least 10 minutes. This resting time allows the meat to finish cooking and the juices to redistribute evenly throughout the steak. It is extremely important to achieving a properly cooked steak when everything is said and done, so despite the temptation, don't skip this step!
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 Use a sharp knife to slice the steak against the grain and serve hot, warm, or room temperature. Skirt steak is particularly flavorful, so any cold leftovers are more than usually delicious.
ca73de78-c274-4294-ade9-768c75c12255 Perfectly grilled steak is perfectly tasty with just salt and pepper.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Gather your ingredients.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Separate the yolks from the whites. Reserve the yolks for another use.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Beat the whites until they are a little frothy. Add salt and pepper, about a 1/2 teaspoon of each.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Chop the vegetables to your desired size.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Heat the olive oil in a non-stick or cast iron skillet.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Lower the heat to low. Pour the egg whites into the pan and swirl them until they completely coat the bottom of the pan.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Use your spatula to pull the egg whites to the center, exposing parts of the pan and allowing the eggs to fill the exposed parts so that it cooks completely.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa When the egg has almost set add the chopped vegetables and cheese to half of the omelet.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Fold the half of the omelet that doesn't have filling over the filling. Cook for another 30 seconds to a minute or until the filling is warmed.
bcf519cf-562f-4d2e-a8d9-c0df318d2daa Serve with more chopped veggies and dig in!
1bd45848-b0c3-40b4-bc34-a07fce10bd00 Gather your ingredients.
1bd45848-b0c3-40b4-bc34-a07fce10bd00 Beat the eggs with a whisk until the yolks and whites are completely combined. Season the eggs with salt and pepper.
1bd45848-b0c3-40b4-bc34-a07fce10bd00 Heat the olive oil in a non-stick or cast iron skillet over medium-low heat. Swirl the olive oil to completely coat the pan. Then turn the heat down to low.
1bd45848-b0c3-40b4-bc34-a07fce10bd00 Add the eggs to the pan, swirling quickly to cover the bottom. Adjust the heat if needed so that the bottom doesn't brown too quickly.
1bd45848-b0c3-40b4-bc34-a07fce10bd00 Use a rubber spatula to move the eggs from the edge to the center, exposing parts of the pan so that the egg can completely cook. Then leave the eggs undisturbed and allow them to cook until the omelet is almost set.
1bd45848-b0c3-40b4-bc34-a07fce10bd00 When the omelet is almost set, spoon the warmed tomato sauce over half of it. Cover the tomato sauce with the shredded cheese and pepperoni. Cook for 30 seconds, until the bottom is just about to brown.
1bd45848-b0c3-40b4-bc34-a07fce10bd00 Fold the omelet in half. Cook for another 30 seconds or so, until the cheese is melted and everything is heated through.
1bd45848-b0c3-40b4-bc34-a07fce10bd00 Serve with a little chopped basil or parsley if you wish and dig in!
6bd7159a-5253-4319-93f8-010bc597ba60 Gather the ingredients.
6bd7159a-5253-4319-93f8-010bc597ba60 In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, salt, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, and allspice.
6bd7159a-5253-4319-93f8-010bc597ba60 Slice the French bread into slices that are at least 1-inch thick. You can use a whole-grain French loaf, but any French or Italian bread should work nicely. Slice at a slight angle to make a longer piece of bread.
6bd7159a-5253-4319-93f8-010bc597ba60 Soak each slice in the egg custard mixture. Turn the slices until all of the mixture has been absorbed into the bread. Depending on how stale the bread is, this may take from 5 to 10 minutes. The secret to this recipe is to completely saturate the bread. This is why thick slices of stale bread are used since thinner fresh bread would fall apart too easily. Make sure to flip the bread so all sides can soak evenly.
6bd7159a-5253-4319-93f8-010bc597ba60 Preheat oven to 400 F. In a large non-stick skillet over medium heat, very lightly brown the slices in the butter and oil for about 2 minutes per side. Don't make it too dark as it will also be baking in the oven.
6bd7159a-5253-4319-93f8-010bc597ba60 From the frying pan or skillet, transfer to a baking sheet or casserole dish. Bake for 10 minutes. After 10 minutes, remove from the oven, turn over, and put back in the oven for another 5 minutes to brown on the other side.
6bd7159a-5253-4319-93f8-010bc597ba60 Traditionally, pain perdu is served with powdered sugar sprinkled over the top. If you want it to look like it would in the French Quarter, then dust away and dig in. You can also top it with maple syrup or fruit sauces like jellies, jams, or marmalades.
6bd7159a-5253-4319-93f8-010bc597ba60 Serve and enjoy!
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 Gather the ingredients.
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 In a small mixing bowl, combine the flour, cocoa powder, sugar, baking soda, and salt. Mix well.
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 In a medium mixing bowl, combine the milk, egg, canola oil, and peppermint extract (if using). Mix well.
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and mix just until combined. The mixture will be lumpy.
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add 1 teaspoon of the butter and let melt, coating the pan. Add about 1/4 cup of batter to form a pancake. Repeat 1 to 3 more times, depending on the size of the skillet, and space the pancakes evenly apart without touching.
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 Let cook for 1 to 2 minutes, or until the edges are setting up and bubbles have formed on the top of the pancake and are beginning to pop.
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 Flip and cook another 1 to 2 minutes, or until cooked through. Keep pancakes warm under a kitchen towel or in a low heat oven.
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 Add another teaspoon of butter and repeat until all of the batter is cooked.
5ea72d64-44bf-4655-acd2-faf94ee4cf39 To serve, top each pile of warm pancakes with chocolate sauce, chocolate chips, mini marshmallows, and peppermint candy.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Gather the ingredients.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly oil a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and set aside.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 In a medium-sized mixing bowl, sift together the flour, white sugar, dark brown sugar, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the soy milk and cider vinegar and let it stand for 2 minutes.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Add the mashed banana, canola oil, maple syrup, and vanilla extract, whisking until well combined.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Add the dry ingredients to the wet, mixing until just combined (do not overmix).
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Fold in the chopped nuts (if using) and pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Bake for about 1 hour, or until a toothpick inserted into the center emerges clean.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Allow the bread to cool on a wire cooling rack for 20 minutes before serving.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Serve warm or at room temperature.
27e9a834-9aed-42b0-b33a-015f9c31f1b9 Enjoy!
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Gather the ingredients.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Line a muffin tin with paper baking cups. Preheat the oven to 400 F.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Melt butter for muffin base, set aside to cool. Combine all of the streusel ingredients together in a small bowl and set aside.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Combine cooled, melted butter with sour cream, whole milk, and egg in a large measuring cup. Beat until completely combined.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Blend flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt in a mixing bowl. Stir until well-combined.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry mixture. Be really careful to not over mix. Just make sure there aren't any dry ingredients left in the bowl.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Then gently fold in the chopped strawberries and rhubarb.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Use a small ice cream scoop or rubber spatula to scoop the batter into the paper lined muffin tins, fill to about 3/4 of the way full.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Top each muffin with about a tablespoon of the streusel topping.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Bake in the oven for about 20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
86b31504-4102-42a4-925d-856cbfc472c1 Serve and enjoy!
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Gather the ingredients.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Heat a cast iron griddle or pan on medium heat before you begin. Make sure it is nice and hot and then lower the temperature before you begin cooking the pancakes.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Beat together the egg, milk, and melted butter.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Whisk in the vanilla and coconut extracts and shredded coconut.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Whisk together the flour, baking powder, and salt in a separate bowl.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Slowly whisk in the egg and milk mixture. It's okay for the batter to be a little lumpy; be careful not to over mix. Let it sit for about 5 minutes. The batter will puff up. If it is too thick, add a little more milk.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Grease the griddle. Spoon the batter in about a 1/4 cup portions on the griddle and let it cook for a few minutes per side.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Keep the pancakes warm in a 200 F oven.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Whisk together the whole milk, powdered sugar, vanilla extract, and coconut extract together.
e3683d28-0548-4e50-8878-0283d8635793 Drizzle the glaze over the pancakes and top them with the toasted coconut.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Gather the ingredients.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Heat the milk, butter, and sugar in a saucepan over medium heat, getting it to a simmer, but not a boil. Remove from the heat and let it cool to lukewarm. This may take 10 minutes or so. You can transfer it to the fridge in another bowl if you need to speed up the process.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Pour the yeast over the top of the milk mixture and stir to combine.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Add 7 cups of the flour and stir together gently.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Cover with a towel and put it in a warm place to rise for about 1 hour.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Add the rest of the flour and the baking powder and stir to combine.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Divide the dough into two or three large pieces.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Roll out one piece at a time into a large rectangle. Leave it relatively thick, about 1/2 inch. Make sure the rectangle is long, width-wise. (Think hot dog, not hamburger.)
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Pour about 3/4 cup of butter over the dough and sprinkle about half the cinnamon and sugar over the top.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Top with half of the dried fruits and chopped pecans.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Roll the dough away from you in a tight roll until it is completely rolled up. Pinch the seam together and then cut into 2-inch slices.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Bring the two ends of the roll together and pinch them together. Gently transfer onto a parchment lined baking sheet.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Cut large slits 3/4 of the way through the dough, make about 10 cuts. Turn each cut section onto its side.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Brush the top of the ring with melted butter and cover gently with a cloth. Repeat with the rest of the dough. Let it rise for about 30 minutes. While it is rising, preheat the oven to 375 F.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Bake rolls for about 25 minutes, do not over bake. They should be lightly brown and slightly firm to the touch. Tent with some foil if it is browning too quickly.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Whisk together the powdered sugar, milk, almond extract, and vanilla extract. If it is too thick add a little more milk, if it is too thin add a little more powdered sugar.
605454db-5948-4280-8115-e20ac716ec70 Remove rings from the oven and if you can manage let them cool a bit and then drizzle icing over the top, slice and serve!
ae34649c-5b6c-442b-badd-4d6b8ca1855b Gather the ingredients.
ae34649c-5b6c-442b-badd-4d6b8ca1855b Sift the flour to bring in more air and combine with sugar, baking powder, and salt in a large bowl until well mixed.
ae34649c-5b6c-442b-badd-4d6b8ca1855b Mix in the soy milk or milk substitute of choice and oil and beat together until batter is smooth. If choosing to use the apple cider vinegar tablespoon remember to remove one tablespoon of the milk substitute before adding it to the mix to avoid a runny batter.
ae34649c-5b6c-442b-badd-4d6b8ca1855b Drop 1/4 cup of batter at a time onto a hot oiled griddle or a well greased frying pan over medium-high heat.
ae34649c-5b6c-442b-badd-4d6b8ca1855b When bubbles appear on the surface of the pancake, approximately 3 minutes, flip and cook the other side for another 2 minutes.​
ae34649c-5b6c-442b-badd-4d6b8ca1855b Serve with your favorite toppings and enjoy!
dde8a5fd-85a4-4e15-a242-60d160bed9f8 Gather the ingredients.
dde8a5fd-85a4-4e15-a242-60d160bed9f8 Break the eggs into a wide, shallow bowl or pie plate and beat them lightly with a fork or whisk.
dde8a5fd-85a4-4e15-a242-60d160bed9f8 Stir the milk, sugar, and salt into the beaten eggs.
dde8a5fd-85a4-4e15-a242-60d160bed9f8 Coat a skillet or griddle with a thin layer of butter. Place it over medium-low heat.
dde8a5fd-85a4-4e15-a242-60d160bed9f8 Place the bread slices, one at a time, into the bowl or plate. Let the bread soak up the egg mixture for a few seconds and then carefully turn to coat the other side. Coat only as many slices as you will be cooking at one time to prevent soggy French toast.
dde8a5fd-85a4-4e15-a242-60d160bed9f8 Transfer the egg-coated bread slices to the hot skillet or griddle. Heat slowly until the bottom is golden brown. Turn and brown the other side.
dde8a5fd-85a4-4e15-a242-60d160bed9f8 Serve French toast hot with butter and syrup, or your preferred toppings. Enjoy.
11d0beed-3e06-4a24-9581-745a0a663fc7 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
11d0beed-3e06-4a24-9581-745a0a663fc7 Generously grease a muffin tin with cooking spray or butter.
11d0beed-3e06-4a24-9581-745a0a663fc7 Press 2 to 3 tater tots or hash browns into each muffin well so that it completely covers the bottom.
11d0beed-3e06-4a24-9581-745a0a663fc7 Whisk together the eggs, milk, and salt and pepper in a small bowl or measuring cup. Pour the egg mixture over each muffin well until the hash browns are completely covered.
11d0beed-3e06-4a24-9581-745a0a663fc7 Top each omelet with an equal amount of the thawed, drained spinach and the shredded cheddar.
11d0beed-3e06-4a24-9581-745a0a663fc7 Place in the oven for about 15 to 20 minutes. The top will be golden brown and the egg will be cooked all the way through. The bake time might be longer, depending on your oven!
11d0beed-3e06-4a24-9581-745a0a663fc7 Let the omelet bites cool slightly and then use a knife separate the omelets from the muffin tin. Serve with hot sauce or a garnish of chives if you wish.
29aefeae-30ba-4cfb-97ce-974d3fa360ca Gather the ingredients.
29aefeae-30ba-4cfb-97ce-974d3fa360ca Preheat the oven to 400 F.
29aefeae-30ba-4cfb-97ce-974d3fa360ca Brush each pita with the olive oil and place directly on the oven rack. Bake for about 7 minutes, or until lightly brown and toasty.
29aefeae-30ba-4cfb-97ce-974d3fa360ca Beat together the cream cheese, vanilla extract, and sugar until smooth. If you make sure the cream cheese is softened, it will blend together much easier!
29aefeae-30ba-4cfb-97ce-974d3fa360ca Stir together the berries and sugar in a medium-sized bowl. Place in the refrigerator if necessary. You may also add lemon juice to the mixture if you like!
29aefeae-30ba-4cfb-97ce-974d3fa360ca Take the pita out of the oven and allow it to cool. Place on a cooling rack so that the pita does not get soggy.
29aefeae-30ba-4cfb-97ce-974d3fa360ca Spread the cream cheese mixture onto each pita and top with an even portion of the berry mixture. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and garnish with mint and enjoy!
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Gather the ingredients.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec In a heavy skillet, spread the sugar in an even layer.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Cook it over medium heat until it starts to melt and turn brown. Slowly swirl the pan or use a silicone or wooden spatula to gently fold the liquifying sugar from the edges into the center.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Remove the pan from the heat as soon as the sugar becomes an amber liquid. Reserve.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Add the brown sugar to a heavy saucepan.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Pour the boiling water over it and let it dissolve without stirring.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Add the caramelized sugar to the melted brown sugar in the saucepan. Simmer, stirring frequently until the mixture thickens to a syrupy consistency.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Remove the pan from the heat and whisk in the butter and maple or vanilla extract.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Use immediately, or let cool before storing in an airtight container.
7a9b2a81-c729-42e5-b13a-2ce928bbbbec Enjoy.
d54e4c0d-2a18-4191-b7ba-51c5f3bbe05b Preheat the oven to 350 F.
d54e4c0d-2a18-4191-b7ba-51c5f3bbe05b Whisk together the eggs, milk, and salt and pepper together. Grease a casserole dish and pour the egg into the dish.
d54e4c0d-2a18-4191-b7ba-51c5f3bbe05b Place the breakfast sausage into another casserole dish. Flatten completely until it is one even layer. Place both baking dishes in the oven. Bake for about 15-20 minutes or until completely cooked. The sausage should be about 170 F in order to be completely cooked.
d54e4c0d-2a18-4191-b7ba-51c5f3bbe05b Slice the rolls so that you have a top and a bottom.
d54e4c0d-2a18-4191-b7ba-51c5f3bbe05b Lay the cooked sausage over the bottom of the rolls, top with the cooked egg and the slices of cheese. Put the top of the rolls back on and place in the oven again. Once the cheese has melted, take the rolls out and cut them into the sliders.
d54e4c0d-2a18-4191-b7ba-51c5f3bbe05b You can also wait to bake them and wrap them individually and freeze them. Reheat them individually later.
e5bd87ba-0ac3-4595-84cf-1c633263a549 Whisk together the pie filling, whole milk, and maple syrup in a medium sized bowl until smooth and completely combined. Make sure there aren't any lumps of the pie filling.
e5bd87ba-0ac3-4595-84cf-1c633263a549 Stir the oats and any of the optional ingredients into the pumpkin pie mixture. Cover the bowl or put it the oatmeal in small glass jars with lids. Place them in the refrigerator overnight, or for at least 4 hours to soften the oats.
e5bd87ba-0ac3-4595-84cf-1c633263a549 After it has sat overnight heat in the microwave if you wish, or just eat cold! Oatmeal will keep in the refrigerator for 3 or 4 days.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e Gather the ingredients.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e Preheat the oven to 360 F and prepare a 12-cup muffin tin either with liners or by lightly coating it with nonstick spray.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e In a large bowl, mash the bananas with a fork until soft.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e Add the oil or vegan margarine and sugar; mix until creamy.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e In a separate bowl, combine the flour, salt, and baking soda until well mixed. Add the flour mixture to the banana mixture, stirring gently just to combine. Don't overmix. The batter will be thick.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e If you're using the walnuts, now is the time to gently fold them in. Alternatively, you can sprinkle them on top of each individual muffin before baking.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e Carefully spoon the batter into the muffin tins, filling each well about 2/3 full. If desired, sprinkle the organic sugar on top just before baking.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e Bake the muffins for about 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Let cool a few minutes and enjoy while still warm or cool completely for longer storage.
db35ea05-6d74-4e0b-af60-aa29b014b52e Enjoy.
f90e1e70-0379-4f02-a293-9773edf999b3 Add the fresh cranberries to a small saucepan. Turn on the heat and add the granulated sugar and water. Stir to combine and allow to come to a boil. Once the cranberries are soft (about 5-10 minutes), turn off the heat. Let cool to lukewarm. Strain the cranberries over a fine mesh sieve. Allow the cranberry mixture to completely cool before making the cocktails.
f90e1e70-0379-4f02-a293-9773edf999b3 Stir the fresh cranberry juice, lime juice, and vodka in a large pitcher. Slowly add the ginger beer and gently stir. If making single serve use about 2 ounces of vodka, 1 Tablespoon of fresh lime juice and top with ginger beer!
f90e1e70-0379-4f02-a293-9773edf999b3 Make sure to serve over ice in copper mugs! They not only look pretty but keep the cocktail super cold! Garnish with lime wedges and fresh cranberries.
36a85037-fc8c-4ef2-8302-a0004583c460 Gather the ingredients.
36a85037-fc8c-4ef2-8302-a0004583c460 Add the fresh cranberries to a small saucepan. Turn on the heat and add the granulated sugar and water. Stir to combine and allow to come to a boil. Once the cranberries are soft (about 5 to10 minutes), turn off the heat. Let cool to lukewarm.
36a85037-fc8c-4ef2-8302-a0004583c460 Strain the cranberries over a fine mesh sieve. Allow the cranberry mixture to completely cool before making the cocktails.
36a85037-fc8c-4ef2-8302-a0004583c460 To make the drinks, shake or stir together the cranberry juice, lime juice, tequila, and orange liquor in a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
36a85037-fc8c-4ef2-8302-a0004583c460 Salt or sugar the rim of the glasses.
36a85037-fc8c-4ef2-8302-a0004583c460 Add ice to each glass and strain the cocktail over the top of the ice.
36a85037-fc8c-4ef2-8302-a0004583c460 Garnish with fresh cranberries and lime wedges.
36a85037-fc8c-4ef2-8302-a0004583c460 Serve and enjoy!
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Gather the ingredients.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Sift together the flour and baking powder in a large mixing bowl.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 In a separate bowl, beat the eggs thoroughly, then stir in the milk, sugar, and salt and mix until the sugar is dissolved. Stir in the vanilla.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Add the wet ingredients to the dry and use a fork to gently and thoroughly combine all of the ingredients. Make sure not to overmix—you'll still see some lumps. Gently break up some of the bigger lumps with your fork, but don't mix for much longer than 20 seconds.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Allow the batter to rest at least 20 minutes.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 If making bigger batches, preheat the oven to 170 F to keep the pancakes warm while you cook the entirety of the batter.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Preheat your griddle to 375 F, or heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 When your cooking surface is hot, lightly spray it with cooking spray.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 For each pancake, ladle 1/4 cup of batter onto the griddle or pan. Cook until the tops of the pancakes are full of bubbles and the bottoms are golden brown.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Flip the pancakes and cook.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Either serve right away or transfer to the oven to keep warm.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Top with the optional butter, fruit and maple syrup, or any toppings of your liking.
8163e746-3ac7-4315-a8f4-12890c940ff9 Enjoy!
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Gather the ingredients.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Preheat the oven to 400 F.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar in a large bowl.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Make sure you have cooled your melted butter to room temperature (oil may also be substituted). Beat together the egg, milk, vanilla, lemon zest, lemon juice, and melted butter together in a mixing cup until completely combined.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients with a whisk.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Pour the wet ingredients into the well, mixing as you pour. Completely combine the ingredients until you have a batter, be careful not to over-mix.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Carefully fold in the raspberries. Be gentle when folding in the raspberries so they do not completely break apart in the batter.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Line a muffin pan with paper cups, or grease the muffin wells with butter or canola spray. Fill the tins to 2/3 of the way full. You can also top the muffins with sparkling sugar before baking.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Bake the muffins for 25 minutes.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Allow them to cool slightly and then slide a knife around the edge of the muffins to release them, if you are not using paper cups.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed To make the glaze, whisk together the powdered sugar, vanilla, lemon juice, and milk.
84568316-f0ea-4e27-bbe1-43fc7aba98ed Drizzle the lemon glaze over the warm muffins and serve!
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Gather the ingredients.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Wash and dry the grapefruits.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Use a sharp vegetable peeler or paring knife, remove the brightly colored zest–and only the brightly colored zest–from the grapefruit. Be sure to leave behind any and all of the white pith directly underneath, it is very bitter.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Chop the resulting zest–bigger pieces for chunkier marmalade, ribbon-like strips for a more spreadable result. Set zest aside.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Cut the ends off the zested grapefruits.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Working with one fruit at a time, cut off the thick white pith from around each grapefruit.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Working over a bowl to catch the juices, hold a fully peeled grapefruit, and use a sharp knife to cut out each section of the membrane holding the sections together.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Squeeze any juice out of the membrane once you've cut out all the fruit.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Set the membrane aside, along with any seeds. The pectin in these will help "set" the marmalade later.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Combine the zest, fruit, juice, 4 cups of water and sugar in a large heavy pot and bring to a boil.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Meanwhile, lay a double layer of cheesecloth in a medium bowl.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Put membranes and seeds in the bowl.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Lift up the corners and tie the cheesecloth into a bag to hold the membranes and seeds.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Add this "pectin bag" to the pot.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 While the mixture comes to a boil, put a canning kettle full of water on to boil if you're planning to can the marmalade.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 In any case, put a few small plates in the freezer to chill them. When the canning kettle water boils, use it to sterilize the jars and lids.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Bring marmalade to 220 F and hold it there for 5 minutes. Be patient, this can take quite a while.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Put a dollop of the mixture on a chilled plate, swirl the plate to spread the mixture a bit, and drag your finger through the mixture. A "set" mixture will hold a clean track behind your finger.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Remove "pectin bag," squeezing any marmalade in it out and back into the pot before discarding the bag.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Take marmalade off the heat and let sit 5 minutes.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Set up clean jars next to the pot.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Stir marmalade to distribute the zest evenly in the mixture.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Use a ladle to transfer the marmalade into the jars, leaving 1/2 inch of headspace at the top of each jar.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 Put lids on the jars.
39929f42-7e7c-4750-9a6d-6c3d6a25e3c9 If you're canning the marmalade, put the jars in the canning kettle and boil for 10 minutes. In any case, let jars cool to room temperature before putting in a cool dry cupboard (if you've hot water processed them) or the fridge (if you didn't hot water process).
3b0aa296-f38f-4eab-8d5c-cbaf385f9181 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
3b0aa296-f38f-4eab-8d5c-cbaf385f9181 Combine all dry ingredients and butter in a food processor, pulse until it forms fine crumbs. If you don't have a food processor use a pastry blender or two forks. Be careful not to over mix or to use your hands. You want the little chunks of butter to stay intact and not melt from the heat of your hands.
3b0aa296-f38f-4eab-8d5c-cbaf385f9181 Add buttermilk as you pulse or mix.
3b0aa296-f38f-4eab-8d5c-cbaf385f9181 Place the dough in a clean bowl. Cut in the shredded cheddar and cooled, cooked sausage until completely incorporated.
3b0aa296-f38f-4eab-8d5c-cbaf385f9181 Separate the dough into 12 balls. Form quickly and gently with your hands so that it is rounded. Place the balls of dough snuggly into a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Brush the tops of each biscuit with melted butter if you wish.
3b0aa296-f38f-4eab-8d5c-cbaf385f9181 Place the casserole dish in the oven and bake for about 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown and cooked all the way through. Serve immediately or allow to cool and cover in aluminum foil and then freeze.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Gather the ingredients.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Sift together the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Make sure you have cooled your melted butter to room temperature (oil may also be substituted). Beat together the egg, milk, sour cream, vanilla, marmalade, and melted butter together in a mixing cup.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients. Pour the wet ingredients into the well, mixing as you pour.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Completely combine the ingredients until you have a batter, be careful not to over-mix. Mix in the cranberries. As it sits, it will thicken slightly.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Line a muffin pan with paper cups, or grease the muffin wells with butter or canola spray. Fill the tins to 2/3 of the way full. You can also top the muffins with sparkling sugar before baking.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Bake the muffins for 25 minutes. Slide a knife around the edge of the muffins to release them, if you are not using paper cups.
3f30b044-971c-4ee8-950e-72d7f91f34dd Serve while still warm!
f4f25b76-35f9-4405-829d-7e57b36c086f In a 12-inch nonstick ovenproof skillet, melt the butter with the olive oil over medium heat.
f4f25b76-35f9-4405-829d-7e57b36c086f Add the onions, garlic, broccoli, and cauliflower. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally with a heatproof spatula until the vegetables are crisp-tender. Then add 2 tablespoons water to the skillet, cover, and steam for 2 minutes, at which point the vegetables should be tender.
f4f25b76-35f9-4405-829d-7e57b36c086f Arrange the pasta on top of the vegetables. Pour the eggs over all and sprinkle with the thyme, salt, and pepper.
f4f25b76-35f9-4405-829d-7e57b36c086f Cook the frittata, lifting the edges occasionally to let uncooked egg flow underneath and wiggling the spatula in the center of the frittata so the egg can flow under and cook evenly until the bottom is lightly browned and the frittata is almost set. Shake the pan occasionally so the frittata doesn't stick.
f4f25b76-35f9-4405-829d-7e57b36c086f Heat the broiler. Place the frittata under the broiler, about 6 inches from the heat source, and broil for another 4 to 8 minutes or just until the egg mixture is set. Remove the skillet from the oven.
f4f25b76-35f9-4405-829d-7e57b36c086f Sprinkle the frittata with both kinds of cheese. Put it back under the broiler. Broil for 3 to 6 minutes longer, rotating the skillet occasionally so it cooks evenly until the cheese is melted and begins to brown.
f4f25b76-35f9-4405-829d-7e57b36c086f Cut the frittata into wedges and serve immediately.
a4828dfc-3c60-4f7a-92a8-5efe011b46cd Preheat oven to 450 F
a4828dfc-3c60-4f7a-92a8-5efe011b46cd Beat the eggs and milk together until smooth.
a4828dfc-3c60-4f7a-92a8-5efe011b46cd Add the flour, sugar, lemon zest, and vanilla and mix until there aren't any lumps. Mix completely and quickly, trying to form a froth if possible.
a4828dfc-3c60-4f7a-92a8-5efe011b46cd Place a skillet in the oven with the butter while it heats.
a4828dfc-3c60-4f7a-92a8-5efe011b46cd When butter is melted, pour the batter into the skillet. Bake for about 15 minutes until fluffy, golden, and not jiggly.
a4828dfc-3c60-4f7a-92a8-5efe011b46cd Whisk together the ingredients for the glaze. Pour the glaze over the hot dutch baby and serve immediately. You can also top with more powdered sugar if you wish!
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c Heat the bourbon in a small saucepan for about two minutes.
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c Remove from the heat and set aside. Butter and flour a 9x5 inch loaf pan or line it with parchment paper.
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c Preheat the oven to 325 F. Whisk together the flour, baking powder and salt in a medium-sized bowl.
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c In the bowl of your stand mixer (or a large bowl) mix together the melted butter and sugar. Beat well until blended. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Then add in the mashed bananas, cooled bourbon, and vanilla extract.
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c Add the flour mixture in thirds to the wet mixture. Stirring gently after each bit. DO NOT OVER MIX.
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c Pour the mixture into the prepared loaf pan and bake on a middle rack in the oven for about one hour. Bake for less time if you are baking on convection.
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c Check its doneness with a toothpick. It should come out fairly clean, but it is ok if it looks a little sticky. This is a very dense and moist bread!
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c Place the loaf pan on a cooling rack.
aa21b0bf-692b-4092-ae21-b373c35ac48c Whisk together the bourbon and powdered sugar until thick and smooth. Once the bread is cooled and removed from the pan, drizzle the glaze over the top of the bread. The bread tastes even better the second day!
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Gather the ingredients.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Preheat oven to 350 F.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 In a large bowl, combine the flour, cocoa powder, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 In a medium bowl, combine the milk, and the melted butter. Then add the oil, whisk in the beaten eggs, and stir in the vanilla extract.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Thoroughly grease and flour a muffin pan (or better yet, you can use paper muffin liners).
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ones and mix no more than 10 seconds. The batter should be visibly lumpy. It's extremely important not to over-mix the batter, or the resulting muffins can be hard or misshapen.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 With a rubber spatula, gently fold 1 cup of chocolate chips into the batter. Don't overwork the batter.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Carefully spoon the batter into the prepared muffin pan (you can use a small ladle or even an ice-cream scoop).
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Sprinkle the remaining chocolate chips onto the tops of the muffins, and transfer to the oven immediately.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of a muffin comes out clean.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Remove the pan from the oven and let the muffins cool for five minutes in the pan.
f2dbea84-4d7d-44b9-abd5-b90da27d0299 Then remove the muffins from the pan and let them cool another five minutes on a wire rack.
636070a0-1db7-4124-847f-5256172074bc Gather the ingredients.
636070a0-1db7-4124-847f-5256172074bc Grease a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish with cooking spray. If making to serve immediately, then preheat the oven to 375 F. If you are refrigerating the french toast overnight, then skip preheating the oven.
636070a0-1db7-4124-847f-5256172074bc Cut the panettone into large slices and layer them into the greased casserole dish.
636070a0-1db7-4124-847f-5256172074bc Whisk together the eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, and orange extract in a medium mixing bowl.
636070a0-1db7-4124-847f-5256172074bc Pour the egg mixture over the top of the panettone. Make sure to coat all of the slices.
636070a0-1db7-4124-847f-5256172074bc Place in the oven uncovered and bake for about 25 to 30 minutes. Let it cool slightly when you remove it from the oven.
636070a0-1db7-4124-847f-5256172074bc Sprinkle it with a little powdered sugar and a drizzle of real maple syrup.
636070a0-1db7-4124-847f-5256172074bc Serve and enjoy!
b6a7a25a-685b-48df-8b9e-c72b64d77ae7 Cook the breakfast sausage according to package directions. Make sure it is completely cooked and that there is no pink, about 170 F is appropriate.
b6a7a25a-685b-48df-8b9e-c72b64d77ae7 In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, salt, and pepper. Cook in a nonstick skillet as for an omelet or scramble them.
b6a7a25a-685b-48df-8b9e-c72b64d77ae7 Spread out the tortillas onto a baking sheet. Place an equal portion of the sausage and egg on each tortilla.
b6a7a25a-685b-48df-8b9e-c72b64d77ae7 Sprinkle an equal amount of shredded cheese on top of each tortilla. Place under the broiler of your oven to melt the cheese. Drizzle each burrito with hot sauce, taco sauce, or salsa.
b6a7a25a-685b-48df-8b9e-c72b64d77ae7 Roll up the burrito and serve.
cf3f4f06-daa7-45c7-bfee-8f49d57a9665 Gather the ingredients.
cf3f4f06-daa7-45c7-bfee-8f49d57a9665 Heat the milk with the butter until the mixture begins to simmer.
cf3f4f06-daa7-45c7-bfee-8f49d57a9665 Combine the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, and salt. Whisk to blend.
cf3f4f06-daa7-45c7-bfee-8f49d57a9665 Add the hot milk mixture to the dry ingredients and stir to blend.
cf3f4f06-daa7-45c7-bfee-8f49d57a9665 Whisk in the beaten egg.
cf3f4f06-daa7-45c7-bfee-8f49d57a9665 Drop onto a hot, greased griddle or drop in an iron skillet and fry until golden brown on both sides.
cf3f4f06-daa7-45c7-bfee-8f49d57a9665 Serve hot with butter and syrup as for pancakes, or serve them as bread with butter.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc Gather the ingredients.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc Preheat the oven to 200 F — this is to keep them warm as you make more batches. Skip this step if you are serving them as they come out of the waffle iron.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc Heat the waffle iron on a medium setting, following the instructions in your waffle iron brochure or manual.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar. Set aside.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc In another bowl, combine the eggs and milk; whisk until well blended. Whisk in the 1/4 cup of melted butter.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc Add the egg and milk mixture to the flour mixture and blend thoroughly. Stir in the corn kernels. If necessary, add more milk to make the batter thin enough to flow when poured into the waffle iron.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc Following the appliance directions, fill the waffle iron with the batter, gently spreading as needed.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc When the first batch is done, remove them to a baking sheet and place them in the preheated oven to keep warm while you cook subsequent batches.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc To serve, drizzle the corn waffles with melted butter and maple syrup or dust them with powdered sugar.
9eaf76bc-84a4-44fb-9e4a-9dcfc8efcefc Enjoy!
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Gather the ingredients.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Beat eggs with cream in a large bowl.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Pour eggs into skillet and cook, stirring frequently, until eggs are scrambled and just set, but still moist.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Remove pan from heat and stir in sour cream.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Spread eggs into a greased 7- x 12-inch glass baking dish and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d When ready to eat, preheat oven to 350 F.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Uncover the baking dish and sprinkle eggs with pepper and salt.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Stir gently, then bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and eggs are hot, at least 145 F on an instant-read thermometer.
335e3311-4e45-4b44-9c08-946a5f68a54d Serve and enjoy!
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Pulse together the flour, shortening and butter, and salt in a food processor until small crumbs form. You can also do this by hand with a pastry blender.
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Gently mix in the beaten egg to the flour mixture.
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Mix vinegar with ice water. Then slowly (Very slowly and very gradually) pour water mixture into food processor while pulsing. Stop when the dough forms large soft crumbs and pulls away from the side of the bowl.
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Remove dough from food processor and divide in half. Gently form the dough into a ball. Place on a piece of saran wrap and cover. Gently flatten with your hand so it makes a short disk. Repeat with the other half of the dough. It is really important not to overwork the dough, because it will become tough very easily.
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Chill in the refrigerator for an hour (30 minutes works if you're short on time!).
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Roll one ball of dough into a long rectangle. Leave the other ball of dough in the refrigerator so it will stay cold while you work with this dough. Cut into eight even rectangles.
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Place four of the rectangles on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet. Spread about a Tablespoon of jam onto each rectangle, leaving a nice little border around the edges. Lay a rectangle over each jammed rectangle. Use a fork to crimp the edges together. Then pierce the top of each pop tart about four times with the tines of a fork.
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Repeat with the other ball of dough.
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Flash freeze the pop tarts in the freezer for about an hour (or longer if need be).
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Bake the pop tarts for about 25 minutes, or until very lightly brown.
6fbaed13-4a30-4c7d-bca1-11a78c252fa4 Whisk together the powdered sugar and milk. Spread the frosting over the cooled pop tarts and sprinkle with sprinkles if desired.
8049405c-9c45-425b-ad07-fb7c79c739d1 Gather the ingredients and equipment.
8049405c-9c45-425b-ad07-fb7c79c739d1 Preheat the oven to 400 F. Position the cooking rack in the middle of the oven. There will be little to no splattering as the bacon cooks.
8049405c-9c45-425b-ad07-fb7c79c739d1 Line the jelly roll pan with the tinfoil to catch all of the grease, so you can just lift off the tinfoil and throw it in the trash when you're done.
8049405c-9c45-425b-ad07-fb7c79c739d1 Place a cookie cooling rack on top of the foil lined sheet.
8049405c-9c45-425b-ad07-fb7c79c739d1 Lay out the strips of bacon onto the cooling rack. The strips can touch as they will shrink when cooking. You may have to lay a few pieces of the bacon width-wise as well as length-wise.
8049405c-9c45-425b-ad07-fb7c79c739d1 Place the jelly roll pan in the oven on the middle rack.
8049405c-9c45-425b-ad07-fb7c79c739d1 Cook for about 10 to 12 minutes or until the bacon is cooked to your desired crispiness. It should lift off of the cooling rack easily.
8049405c-9c45-425b-ad07-fb7c79c739d1 Serve and enjoy!
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 Gather the ingredients.
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 Heat 1 to 2 inches of water in a saucepan over medium heat. Also, make sure your clarified butter is warm but not hot.​
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 Combine the egg yolks and the cold water in a glass or stainless steel mixing bowl (not aluminum) and whisk for 1 to 2 minutes, until the mixture is light and foamy. Whisk in a couple of drops of the lemon juice, too.​
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 The water in the saucepan should have begun to simmer.
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 Set the bowl directly atop the saucepan of simmering water. The water itself should not come in contact with the bottom of the bowl. Whisk the eggs for 1 to 2 minutes, until they're slightly thickened.​
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 Remove the bowl from the heat and begin adding the melted butter slowly at first, a few drops at a time, while whisking constantly. If you add it too quickly, the emulsion will break.​
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 Continue beating in the melted butter. As the sauce thickens, you can gradually increase the rate at which you add it, but at first, slower is better.​
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 After you've added all the butter, whisk in the remaining lemon juice and season to taste with kosher salt and cayenne pepper (or a dash of Tabasco sauce).
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 The finished hollandaise sauce will have a smooth, firm consistency. If it's too thick, you can adjust the consistency by whisking in a few drops of warm water.​
9ab06f22-aea7-49e2-9578-5d6f6a6f29d1 Serve and enjoy.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Gather the ingredients.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f In a small bowl, gently mix the yeast with the warm water and let sit until frothy, about 5 minutes.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Meanwhile, in a medium-sized bowl using an electric hand mixer, cream the dairy-free soy margarine and sugar until the fluffy, about 3 minutes.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Add the salt, beating until incorporated. Add the warm almond milk (or another non-dairy milk alternative) and Egg Replacer mixture and beat until combined.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Turn the hand mixer onto a low-speed setting and add the yeast mixture. Once the mixture is combined, add the flour, 1 cup at a time, until the dough is soft, but not sticky.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until elastic.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Place the dough in a lightly oiled bowl. Cover the bowl loosely with a dishtowel or plastic wrap and allow the dough to rise in a warm place for 1 1/2 hours. (We like to set our bowl over a small heatproof dish of hot water to help the dough proof. The bowl itself should not be hot, so we like to heat water in a kettle until steaming, pour about 1 to 2 cups of water in a deep but narrow dish, and set our dough bowl on top.)
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix the dark brown sugar and cinnamon.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Grease (with dairy-free soy margarine) or oil a 9”x13” casserole dish. Set aside.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Preheat the oven to 375 F. Punch down the dough.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Turn the dough out onto a dry surface and roll the dough out into a 12-inch square.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Brush with the melted soy margarine and then sprinkle with the cinnamon-sugar mixture, followed by the raisins, nuts or other desired toppings.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Carefully, using your hands, roll the dough into a log. Pinch together the edges to seal.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Using a sharp knife, slice the log into 8-12 equal pieces. Arrange the pieces in the prepared dish and allow the rolls to rest until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Bake the rolls in the preheated oven for about 18 to 22 minutes, or until golden brown. (A toothpick inserted into the center of one of the rolls should emerge clean when they're ready to come out.)
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Set the rolls on a wire cooling rack to cool slightly before icing with dairy-free icing.
79c998d5-5d49-4517-8611-e4d13cb5790f Serve warm and enjoy!
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Gather the ingredients.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 If your loaf is very large (i.e. Pullman) then slice off the top 2 inches to make the loaf more square than rectangular. If your loaf is average-sized, slice 1/2-inch to an inch off the top.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Slice the loaf in half lengthwise, Open the two halves like a book, so the interior of each half is facing you.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Place a baking sheet on the middle rack in the oven, and preheat to 350 F.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Using a spoon, dig an indentation about 1/2-inch deep along the crust edges of each half, then remove a shallow layer of the bread's interior by gently pulling it out towards you with your fingers. This will give the cheese a small well to melt into. Reserve the scooped-out bread to make breadcrumbs.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Cut a sheet of parchment paper that will fit both halves of the loaf and place it on your work surface. Flip both halves of the bread over so the exteriors are facing you.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Generously spread the tops of the loaf halves (not the interior section with the scooped-out wells) with mayonnaise, then flip over once more and place both halves mayonnaise-side down on the parchment.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Layer the cheese slices into the scooped-out wells in each half: American first, then cheddar, then mozzarella.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Remove the baking sheet from the oven, then quickly transfer the halves from the parchment to the baking sheet, using a spatula if necessary.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Bake for 18-20 minutes, or until cheese on top of both halves is bubbly and browning.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Remove the baking sheet from the oven, then carefully flip the top half of the bread onto the bottom to make a sandwich, and transfer the whole thing to a cooling rack. Let rest for 10 minutes.
ea3f6b47-98d5-444f-941b-0bd466c80492 Make the first slice in the middle (and check out that cheesy pull), then let rest for another 5-10 minutes before slicing individual sandwiches out from the middle of each half of the giant grilled cheese. This will ensure even distribution of cheese within each slice.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 Gather the ingredients.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 Place a trivet in the Instant Pot inner pot and add 3/4 cup of water or stock.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 If the chicken wings are whole, cut them at the joint and cut off the wing tips. Discard the wing tips or freeze them to use in stock. Sprinkle the chicken wings with kosher salt and arrange them on the trivet.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 Lock the lid in place and turn the steam release knob to the sealing position. Choose the manual or pressure cook button (high pressure) and set the timer for 10 minutes. When the time is up, let the pressure come down for 5 minutes and then carefully turn the knob to the venting position to release the remaining pressure.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 In a saucepan, combine the hot sauce, butter, vinegar, black pepper, garlic powder, and cayenne pepper (if using). Bring to a simmer and cook for 1 minute.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 Drain the wings and transfer them to a bowl. Add about half of the sauce mixture and toss them gently.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 Arrange the wings in a single layer on the prepared baking sheets. Broil about 4 to 6 inches from the heat source for 5 minutes. Turn the wings and continue to broil the other side for 4 to 5 minutes longer, or until golden brown.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 Remove the wings to a bowl and drizzle with the remaining sauce mixture.
36ae16e5-fcdc-40e2-8b96-f1d64b147533 Serve Buffalo wings with celery and carrot sticks along with blue cheese or ranch dressing for dipping.
a576f79f-eb56-4391-aaad-e6d5ae9bc222 Gather the ingredients.
a576f79f-eb56-4391-aaad-e6d5ae9bc222 Slice the onions into thin half moons.
a576f79f-eb56-4391-aaad-e6d5ae9bc222 Heat the olive oil in a large sauté pan on medium high heat. Add the sliced onions and salt. Saute on medium low heat, stirring occasionally for 25 to 35 minutes or until the onions are deeply caramelized. They will be so soft that they can easily be mashed with the back of a fork.
a576f79f-eb56-4391-aaad-e6d5ae9bc222 Remove the onions from the pan and allow them to cool.
a576f79f-eb56-4391-aaad-e6d5ae9bc222 Add in the minced shallots, chopped chives, and reserved caramelized onions.
a576f79f-eb56-4391-aaad-e6d5ae9bc222 Serve with potato chips or crudité immediately or cover it with plastic wrap and store in the refrigerator for up to 4 days.
9d57298b-9f73-46f2-a727-8b2142c915cf Gather the ingredients.
9d57298b-9f73-46f2-a727-8b2142c915cf Pat the wings dry with paper towels.
9d57298b-9f73-46f2-a727-8b2142c915cf Spread them out in a single layer and sprinkle with the salt, pepper, garlic powder, and cayenne pepper.
