9d57298b-9f73-46f2-a727-8b2142c915cf Place all of the wings in the air fryer and set for 380 F. Cook for 25 minutes. Pause the air fryer and toss the wings every five minutes.
9d57298b-9f73-46f2-a727-8b2142c915cf Turn the heat up on the air fryer to 400 F and cook for another 5 to 10 minutes until crispy and browned. You can cook the wings in a single layer in two batches for even more crispiness.
9d57298b-9f73-46f2-a727-8b2142c915cf To make the sauce, melt the butter in the microwave for one minute or until melted. Whisk in the garlic powder and hot sauce until completely combined. Place it back in the microwave for one to two minutes to heat thoroughly. Make sure the sauce is at least warm before you toss it with the wings.
9d57298b-9f73-46f2-a727-8b2142c915cf Add the wings to a large bowl. Drizzle the sauce over the top and toss to coat. Serve the wings immediately topped with chopped chives and alongside your favorite dipping sauce.
963f73f4-c6db-4912-bd7d-cd6e6ea8c63c Gather the ingredients for the tots.
963f73f4-c6db-4912-bd7d-cd6e6ea8c63c Spread the tater tots over an aluminum-lined baking sheet. Bake in a 425 F oven until golden brown, about 25 minutes.Turn halfway through baking to make sure they are crispy on all sides.
963f73f4-c6db-4912-bd7d-cd6e6ea8c63c Gather the ingredients for the chipotle queso.
963f73f4-c6db-4912-bd7d-cd6e6ea8c63c While the tots are baking, heat the queso in a small crockpot or in the microwave until smooth and completely melted. Stir the queso frequently until it has melted.
963f73f4-c6db-4912-bd7d-cd6e6ea8c63c Layer the pepper jack cheese over the crispy tots and place the pan back in the oven until the cheese has melted and is browned slightly.
963f73f4-c6db-4912-bd7d-cd6e6ea8c63c Heat up your taco or al pastor meat if needed. Spread the meat over the totchos and then top with some of the chipotle queso, onions, jalapenos, scallions, and more pepper jack if you want them extra cheesy.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a Gather your ingredients.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a Beat the cream cheese until completely smooth and fluffy. Preheat the oven to 375 F.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a Add the chopped scallions, garlic, sour cream, mayonnaise, crab, salt, and pepper to taste, and 1 tablespoon of sweet chili sauce to the bowl of whipped cream cheese.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a Fold the ingredients together in the bowl with a spatula until completely combined. Break up the crab as finely as you like.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a Pour the mixture into a greased baking dish. You can decide what size dish you want. An 8-inch round casserole will work well, but choose the shape you like best.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a If you are adding the mozzarella cheese, sprinkle it over the top of the dip before popping it in the preheated oven.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a While the dip is baking, prepare the wonton chips. Cut the wrappers into triangles or chip like shapes. Using egg roll wrappers work just as well as wonton wrappers and they are often a little thicker.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a Heat the oil to the deep frying temperature of 375 F and monitor it with a frying or candy thermometer.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a Add the wrappers into the hot oil in batches of 4 or 5 at a time, depending on the size of your pot. Flip the wontons quickly so that they are lightly golden and fried on both sides. Drain them on a paper towel-lined plate or baking sheet.
c4e49100-101e-44b9-b7f1-10be9ee6531a Take the dip out of the oven when the cheese is brown and the dip is heated through the center, about 20 minutes. Drizzle the remaining sweet chili sauce over the top of the dip. Then top with more chopped scallions. Start dipping and enjoy.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Gather the ingredients.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Cook the bacon bits in a frying pan until brown and crispy. Drain on a paper towel and set aside. Leave the bacon grease in the pan and set it aside as well.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Leave about half of the bacon grease in the frying pan. Add the breadcrumbs to the pan and toast over low heat until evenly browned. Shake the pan frequently to prevent the breadcrumbs from burning.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Add the cream cheese, jalapenos, scallions, cheddar, salt, and garlic powder to a large bowl. Make sure the cream cheese is soft enough to stir.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Mix together the ingredients with a spoon or hand mixer until they are completely incorporated and evenly distributed. Taste to make sure it's salty and spicy enough to your liking.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Form the cream cheese mixture into a ball and then flatten the top and pinch the sides into a football shape. Using slightly damp hands will prevent the cream cheese from sticking to your hands too much.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Cover the cheese ball with plastic wrap and place it in the refrigerator for 20 minutes to firm up slightly.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Cover the cheeseball with the toasted breadcrumbs and then press in the bacon bits.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Cut the cheese into strips to make the football laces. Place the smaller strips horizontally with a half inch in between them. Then lay the longer strip vertically over the horizontal strips.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 For a more vibrant look (and so people know it's spicy!), add the chopped fresh jalapenos and some scallions to the top of the football.
c2f735ee-0096-4b99-9cd8-06026d473a77 Serve with pretzels and crackers.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 Gather the ingredients.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 Add the flour, yeast, salt, water, and one tablespoon of the olive oil to a bowl and stir until it becomes a shaggy dough.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 Use your hands to help the dough come together into a loose dough. Place the dough in a oiled bowl and allow to rise, covered, for one hour.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 If you are making smaller rolls, divide the dough into two to four balls. If you are not, you can use the dutch oven method below to create the bowl.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 Pre-heat the oven to 475 F. Place a medium sized dutch oven in the oven to heat for 15 minutes. Form the dough into a single, tight ball and place it on a piece of parchment paper. Transfer it to the hot dutch oven and bake, covered for 30 minutes.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 After 30 minutes, remove the lid and bake uncovered for an additional 15 minutes, or until browned.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 Allow the bread to cool for ten minutes. Then cut a lid off of the top of the loaf and set aside.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 Dig out the inside of the bread to remove most of the soft bread. Cut the top of the bread lid into cubes.
49f7c8b2-2c5a-4c86-9348-30a0705b5296 Brush the inside of the bread bowl with the remaining olive oil and bake again for 10 minutes to toast the inside of the bread bowl. Do this especially if you want to serve soup inside the bread bowl. It will keep the soup from making the bread bowl too soggy.
9f31966f-4332-45f7-bec7-3e33e1107f33 Gather the ingredients.
9f31966f-4332-45f7-bec7-3e33e1107f33 Chop the tomatoes. You may want to remove excess seeds and pulp.
9f31966f-4332-45f7-bec7-3e33e1107f33 Chop the fresh basil.
9f31966f-4332-45f7-bec7-3e33e1107f33 Combine the tomatoes, oil, basil, and salt in a covered bowl and let marinate at least 4 hours. Do not refrigerate as the tomatoes will lose their flavor in the refrigerator.
9f31966f-4332-45f7-bec7-3e33e1107f33 Immediately before serving, toast the bread slices lightly.
9f31966f-4332-45f7-bec7-3e33e1107f33 Use a slotted spoon to layer the tomato basil mixture onto bread.
9f31966f-4332-45f7-bec7-3e33e1107f33 Crack fresh pepper over the top. Serve immediately.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Gather the ingredients.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Pour about 2 inches of the canola oil to a heavy bottom skillet or cast iron pan and heat to 350 F.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Add the egg white to a small bowl and set it aside along with a pastry brush.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Finley dice the corned beef and the Swiss cheese and combine in a bowl.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Drain the sauerkraut into a fine mesh strainer and squeeze it as dry as you can. Add it to the bowl with the diced corned beef and Swiss cheese.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Place each egg roll wrapper with one of the corners facing you so it looks like a diamond.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Spread a few tablespoons of the filling in a horizontal line. Be sure to leave about one inch of empty space on either side.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Roll the corner that's closest to you over the filling and tuck it slightly under the filling.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Brush the two sides with the egg white (you can also use your finger) and fold the left and right corners in.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Fold forward one more time, brush the remaining flap with the egg white, and seal shut. (Most egg roll wrapper packages will have a handy illustration on the back of how to fold the roll.)
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Fry the egg rolls in batches (don't overcrowd the pan) for a minute or two on each side until golden brown. Remove to a paper towel-lined plate and sprinkle with a bit of sea salt.
43ed5308-3272-447b-890c-f568cba84249 Serve with store bought Russian dressing or make your own by combining mayonnaise with ketchup.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Gather the ingredients.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, ketchup, horseradish, garlic powder, paprika, oregano, salt, black pepper, and cayenne pepper. Stir to blend. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Cut the top off the onion and remove the outer peel.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Place the onion on a cutting board, cut-side down. With a sharp knife, make a cut about 1/2-inch from the root.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Make three more evenly spaced cuts around the onion. You will have 4 evenly spaced portions. Make sure you leave the root intact.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Make 2 to 3 cuts in the center of each quarter. You should have 12 to 16 cuts, depending on the size of the onion.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Turn the onion over and separate the petals slightly.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Place the onion in a bowl of ice water and let stand for 1 to 2 hours. Remove the onion to paper towels to drain.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Place the onion in a bowl and sift the flour over it while gently separating the petals. You might have to do this a few times to get good coverage. Gently turn the onion upside-down to shake off any excess.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d In a bowl, whisk the eggs with the buttermilk. Place the onion in a bowl and pour the egg mixture over it, gently separating the petals. Remove the onion to a wide, shallow bowl.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Combine the breadcrumbs and Old Bay seasoning; sprinkle over the onion petals.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Set the air fryer temperature to 375 F and preheat the following the manufacturer's directions. Spray the tray with cooking oil spray and add the onion, root-side down. Cook for 15 minutes.
00aa8852-08bd-40b9-bf2e-eb6c1b23103d Serve the blooming onion immediately with the dip.
0c3b128c-9f6c-40fa-b659-084b96fdb837 Gather the ingredients.
0c3b128c-9f6c-40fa-b659-084b96fdb837 Peel 1 pound shallots. Trim both ends and separate the cloves. Set aside.
0c3b128c-9f6c-40fa-b659-084b96fdb837 In a wide, nonreactive saucepan (stainless steel or enamel but not aluminum), combine 1 1/2 cups white-wine vinegar, 1/2 cup sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve the sugar.
0c3b128c-9f6c-40fa-b659-084b96fdb837 Add the peeled shallots and stir to coat evenly. Cook briskly for exactly 1 minute and remove from the heat.
0c3b128c-9f6c-40fa-b659-084b96fdb837 Submerge the sprig of savory in the pickling liquid. Allow the mixture to stand until it cools to room temperature.
0c3b128c-9f6c-40fa-b659-084b96fdb837 Transfer to an impeccably clean or sterilized glass bowl or jar with a lid.
0c3b128c-9f6c-40fa-b659-084b96fdb837 Cover the bowl or cap the jar and refrigerate for at least 1 week before tasting. Shallots will keep this way for up to 2 months.
0c3b128c-9f6c-40fa-b659-084b96fdb837 Serve as an appetizer with wooden picks, or use as a salad component or part of a relish tray.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 Gather the ingredients.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 Heat a gas or charcoal grill to high heat. Ideally, the grill should hit 500 F.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 In a small saucepan, gently melt the butter.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 Mix the melted butter with the garlic, pepper, and oregano. Reserve in a small bowl.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 Place the oysters on the half shell right over the hottest part. The oyster shouldn't be cut loose from the shell as they can slip and fall right through the grill.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 Spoon enough of the seasoned butter over the oysters so that some of it will overflow into the fire and flame up a bit.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 The oysters are ready when they puff up and get curly on the sides, about 5 minutes.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 In a small bowl, mix together the grated Parmesan and Romano cheeses. Reserve.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 Top with the cheese mix and parsley.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 Serve on the shells immediately.
c65e905d-6522-4cf6-acc8-a3a3595abc35 Enjoy.
b6aa8c3e-b369-4386-be85-db45fb3143b0 Gather the ingredients.
b6aa8c3e-b369-4386-be85-db45fb3143b0 In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, milk, salt, garlic powder, and cayenne pepper or Tabasco sauce, to taste. Blend well.
b6aa8c3e-b369-4386-be85-db45fb3143b0 Gently fold in the chopped crabmeat.
b6aa8c3e-b369-4386-be85-db45fb3143b0 Cover and refrigerate the crab dip until it is thoroughly chilled.
b6aa8c3e-b369-4386-be85-db45fb3143b0 Serve this creamy crab dip with chips, crackers, or raw vegetable dippers.
39ea5681-d771-4a62-abff-0fabe9d9c979 In a bowl combine cream cheese, drained crushed pineapple, chopped bell pepper, chopped green onion, seasoned salt, and 1 cup of the chopped pecans. Mix well to blend ingredients.
39ea5681-d771-4a62-abff-0fabe9d9c979 Chill the cream cheese mixture in refrigerator until it's quite firm and then shape into a ball. Return it to the refrigerator until serving time.
39ea5681-d771-4a62-abff-0fabe9d9c979 Put the remaining chopped pecans in a container. Cover and set aside until serving time.
39ea5681-d771-4a62-abff-0fabe9d9c979 Just before serving, roll the cheese ball in the remaining cup of chopped pecans.
39ea5681-d771-4a62-abff-0fabe9d9c979 Serve with assorted crackers or with simple baked crostini slices (see below) or croutons. It would be a delicious spread to serve with slices of ham as well.
39ea5681-d771-4a62-abff-0fabe9d9c979 Makes about 3 cups of pineapple cheese spread.
cc697a21-8bc6-4960-b7d3-fc61a7f10155 Gather the ingredients.
cc697a21-8bc6-4960-b7d3-fc61a7f10155 Preheat oven to 375 F.
cc697a21-8bc6-4960-b7d3-fc61a7f10155 Slice pita open so that one side is smooth and the other side is rough. Place open pita rounds, with the rough side up, on a cookie sheet.
cc697a21-8bc6-4960-b7d3-fc61a7f10155 Mix oil and zaatar in a small bowl. A pinch of salt can be added if desired.
cc697a21-8bc6-4960-b7d3-fc61a7f10155 Brush the rough side of the pita rounds with the zaatar and oil mix.
cc697a21-8bc6-4960-b7d3-fc61a7f10155 Toast the pita with za'atar for approximately 6 to 8 minutes or until just lightly browned.
5df6cf17-b158-4df1-befd-91c1914004fc Gather the ingredients.
5df6cf17-b158-4df1-befd-91c1914004fc If you've got a food processor, you can process all the ingredients for a few seconds. Don't process too finely, since tapenade should not be completely smooth, but more of a thick and chunky paste. Of course, you can also process it to whatever texture you prefer!
5df6cf17-b158-4df1-befd-91c1914004fc Serve the tapenade with crackers, flatbread, baguette, or slices of toasted artisan bread.
5df6cf17-b158-4df1-befd-91c1914004fc Enjoy!
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Gather the ingredients.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Dredge oxtails in the 1/2 cup flour.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Heat the beef drippings or cooking oil in a large, heavy pot over high heat. Cook to brown the meat, remove (keeping the fat in the pan), and drain on paper towels.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Add the minced onions to the pot, turn the heat to medium, and saute 8 to 10 minutes until golden.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Sprinkle in remaining 2 tablespoons flour, mix well, and brown lightly.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Slowly add the water, and stir in tomato paste, salt, and pepper. Tie the bay leaf in cheesecloth with the thyme, cloves, and parsley and add to the pot.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Return oxtail to pot, cover, and simmer 3 hours until meat is fork-tender. Cool and skim off fat; remove cheesecloth bag.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Remove the oxtail from the soup and separate the meat from the bones. Cut the meat into bite-size pieces and return to pot. Add the carrots and celery.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until carrots are tender. If you like, mix in sherry or port.
6fc82857-367c-4596-8600-7bc726c12b95 Serve as is, or strain the liquid and serve as a first course. Follow with oxtail and vegetables.
a7fd8305-c3c9-4859-ba85-4893062dee02 Grate the zucchini on a large-hole grater into a large bowl. Move the zucchini over to one side.
a7fd8305-c3c9-4859-ba85-4893062dee02 Crack the egg into a small bowl and beat it until there is no distinct yolk and white bits. Add the egg to the zucchini and stir them together.
a7fd8305-c3c9-4859-ba85-4893062dee02 Sprinkle the zucchini-egg mixture with the flour and salt and stir to combine thoroughly. Cover and chill for at least 30 minutes and up to several hours.
a7fd8305-c3c9-4859-ba85-4893062dee02 Heat a generous layer of oil (about 1/4 inch deep) in a large frying pan or pot over medium-high heat to 350 F to 375 F. How do you know when it's hot enough? A bit of batter dropped into the pan should sizzle immediately; if it doesn't, give the oil a bit more time to heat up (if it sizzles and browns instantly, then the oil is too hot—reduce the heat and let it cool off a bit).
a7fd8305-c3c9-4859-ba85-4893062dee02 Put generous spoonfuls of batter into the pan. Flatten them a bit with the back of the spoon to make fritter or pancake-shaped items. You should be able to fit about four fritters in a 10-inch frying pan at a time. Cook until the fritters are browned on one side, about 4 minutes. Use a spatula to flip the fritters over and cook until they are brown on both sides, about 4 more minutes. Go more on whether the fritters are browned and cooked through than the time since the exact temperature of the oil and the batter will vary the cooking time.
a7fd8305-c3c9-4859-ba85-4893062dee02 While the fritters cook, line a paper plate or baking sheet with layers of paper towels. When the fritters are brown and tender, transfer them to the paper-towel-lined plate to drain. Repeat with the remaining batter.
a7fd8305-c3c9-4859-ba85-4893062dee02 Serve the fritters immediately. If that's not quite possible, you can keep them warm by popping them in a warm oven (about 200 F), if necessary.
a7fd8305-c3c9-4859-ba85-4893062dee02 Enjoy!
f524a7b1-f97e-41bd-a06d-9d3670abc7e0 Gather the ingredients.
f524a7b1-f97e-41bd-a06d-9d3670abc7e0 Blend all the ingredients into a thick paste, using a small amount of water as necessary to achieve desired consistency.
f524a7b1-f97e-41bd-a06d-9d3670abc7e0 Serve chilled or at room temperature.
f524a7b1-f97e-41bd-a06d-9d3670abc7e0 Enjoy!
5b52d07d-3641-41a6-9623-605a811089bc Gather the ingredients.
5b52d07d-3641-41a6-9623-605a811089bc Either by hand or using an electric mixer, whisk the cream until it has soft peaks and a texture that is similar to whipped cream. Set aside.
5b52d07d-3641-41a6-9623-605a811089bc In a separate bowl, whisk together goat cheese and milk until the goat cheese has softened. Mix in chives. Gently fold in whipped cream.
5b52d07d-3641-41a6-9623-605a811089bc Serve chilled with bread and/or crackers on the side.
1d6b4054-79a6-4d84-8413-b030e11c5b67 Gather the ingredients.
1d6b4054-79a6-4d84-8413-b030e11c5b67 Add the beer, lemon juice, and salt to a large saucepan or stewpot.
1d6b4054-79a6-4d84-8413-b030e11c5b67 Add your steamer basket to the pot, making sure that it sits well above the beer.
1d6b4054-79a6-4d84-8413-b030e11c5b67 Add the celery and shrimp to the basket and cover.
1d6b4054-79a6-4d84-8413-b030e11c5b67 Bring the beer to a boil, then reduce to a simmer.
1d6b4054-79a6-4d84-8413-b030e11c5b67 Cook until all of the shrimp turn pink. The top ones tend to change color first, so make sure to move them around and check that all have turned pink.
1d6b4054-79a6-4d84-8413-b030e11c5b67 Serve warm or cold as they are or with cocktail sauce or melted butter. As these are served with the shell on, remember to provide a bowl for the shells.
1d6b4054-79a6-4d84-8413-b030e11c5b67 Enjoy!
4e99d4ac-9418-490a-ac2b-c5879075fa5c In a large Dutch oven or stockpot, combine potatoes, onions, chicken broth, and black pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
4e99d4ac-9418-490a-ac2b-c5879075fa5c Meanwhile, pour water into a skillet to a depth of about 1/2-inch. Place the skillet over medium-high heat and bring to a boil. Put the sausages in the boiling water.
4e99d4ac-9418-490a-ac2b-c5879075fa5c Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer the sausages for 15 minutes.
4e99d4ac-9418-490a-ac2b-c5879075fa5c Drain and remove the sausage from the casings. Thinly slice the sausage or crumble and set aside.
4e99d4ac-9418-490a-ac2b-c5879075fa5c Blend or process cooked potato mixture, a little at a time, until smooth. Return to the stockpot and add butter and chopped spinach. Cook, uncovered, over low heat for about 3 to 5 minutes, until spinach is wilted. Stir in sliced or crumbled sausage meat; taste and add kosher salt and freshly ground pepper, to taste. Serve immediately.
c7d4fefd-4e9b-4f90-8c04-92f836d2070d Gather the ingredients.
c7d4fefd-4e9b-4f90-8c04-92f836d2070d Melt the butter in a medium saucepan over low heat. Add the flour, stirring with a fork until the mixture is thick and pasty.
c7d4fefd-4e9b-4f90-8c04-92f836d2070d Turn up the heat to medium-low and then slowly add in the milk, whisking it all together and stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
c7d4fefd-4e9b-4f90-8c04-92f836d2070d Add the garlic powder, Italian seasoning (or basil and oregano), salt, and pepper. Allow your sauce to simmer for 3 to 4 minutes, or until it has thickened.
c7d4fefd-4e9b-4f90-8c04-92f836d2070d Stir in the freshly grated Parmesan cheese until the cheese has melted and is well incorporated. Your white sauce will thicken further as it cools, so add a bit more milk if needed and, conversely, don't worry if it seems too thin while on the stovetop over the heat.
c7d4fefd-4e9b-4f90-8c04-92f836d2070d Serve with your favorite pizza crust or pasta.
c7d4fefd-4e9b-4f90-8c04-92f836d2070d Enjoy!
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc Cut off the round, seed-containing part of the squash and reserve it for another recipe. Cut off the stem end of the squash's neck. Slice off the thick skin.
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc Cut the butternut squash into very thin rounds or slices. They should be almost transparent. You can use a mandoline, the slicing blade of a food processor, a vegetable peeler, or a knife (be careful!) to do this.
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc Toss the squash slices with the oil, if using. Use your clean hands to separate the pieces and coat each of them with the oil.
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc Arrange the butternut squash pieces on the trays of your dehydrator, making sure that none of the pieces are overlapping.
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc Dry the squash at 145F/63C (the highest setting on most dehydrators) for 2 hours. Reduce the heat to 110F/43C and dry for an additional 8 - 10 hours.
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc The squash chips should be crisp and curling up (like conventional fried chips), but still bright orange and not showing any signs of discoloration.
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc They may not seem fully crisp while they are still warm: let them cool for 10 minutes with the dehydrator turned off. They will crisp up the way cookies do after they come out of the oven.
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc If after the cooling off period they still aren't crisp, turn the dehydrator back on at 110F/43C and dry them for an additional 1 - 2 hours.
ed60770c-a210-48b6-bd4f-8254853d7abc Sprinkle the salt, if using, over the chips. Eat immediately or transfer, once cooled to room temperature, into airtight containers.
a232a73e-8511-49b4-95b9-40cd4c05e9c4 Place the cheese cubes and salsa in a slow cooker or crock pot. Cover and cook on HIGH, stirring occasionally until the cheese cubes are melted and blended with the salsa, about 2 hours. Stir in fresh chopped cilantro after the cheese has melted or leave them out.
a232a73e-8511-49b4-95b9-40cd4c05e9c4 Serve hot, right from the slow cooker, with tortilla chips or corn chips or assorted crackers.
2fd29657-202f-41a3-9a47-368c5bfd7b17 Dice the cucumbers.
2fd29657-202f-41a3-9a47-368c5bfd7b17 Peel and mince the garlic.
2fd29657-202f-41a3-9a47-368c5bfd7b17 Chop the mint leaves.
2fd29657-202f-41a3-9a47-368c5bfd7b17 Mix all ingredients in a bowl: combine the yogurt, diced cucumbers, garlic, lemon juice, olive oil, salt, pepper, fresh mint, and paprika, stirring well to combine.
2fd29657-202f-41a3-9a47-368c5bfd7b17 Chill the tzatziki in the refrigerator for at least an hour before serving to allow flavors to mingle.
2fd29657-202f-41a3-9a47-368c5bfd7b17 Taste and adjust seasonings. Give it all a quick stir again just before serving. Tzatziki should be served cold.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b Gather the ingredients.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b Preheat the oven to 375 F.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b In a food processor, combine the softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, shredded cheese, 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese, the green chilies, and jalapeños and process until smooth. You do not need to drain the can of jalapeños or the can of chiles, but if you prefer a dip that's a little less creamy, you can omit these juices.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b Spread the dip into a greased 2-quart casserole.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b In a medium bowl, mix the panko breadcrumbs, the remaining 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese, and the melted butter.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b Sprinkle the crumb mixture evenly over the dip.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b Bake for about 20 minutes, or until the top is golden brown, the dip is heated through and bubbles gently on the edges.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b Serve the dip warm with buttery crackers or a sliced French bread.
32b757db-96ae-469a-ad5a-61d74a99070b Enjoy!
df0868b8-50f2-4c0f-81c0-9298fbba4a12 Preheat an oven to 375 F. In a large bowl, combine the oats, flour, sugar, salt, and baking soda. Add the shortening or butter and use two knives, a large fork, or your fingers to work the fat into the dry ingredients.
df0868b8-50f2-4c0f-81c0-9298fbba4a12 Pour in the hot water and stir until everything comes together into a thick, sticky dough.
df0868b8-50f2-4c0f-81c0-9298fbba4a12 You can roll the dough out on a well-floured surface and cut it into shapes, and set them on a large baking sheet. Or, keep things simple and simply press the dough into an even 1/4-inch layer on a baking sheet. Score this large "cake" into smaller pieces: use a knife to cut the dough into squares or rectangles or whatever shapes you like, but don't bother to separate the pieces; the pieces will bake back together, but be easy to cut or break along that original cut-line.
df0868b8-50f2-4c0f-81c0-9298fbba4a12 Bake until golden, about 12 minutes. You can take them out now for chewier oatcakes or reduce the oven to 325 F and bake until lightly browned, about 10 more minutes, for crisper oatcakes.
df0868b8-50f2-4c0f-81c0-9298fbba4a12 When they have finished baking, if you've cut them into shapes, let them cool; if you've scored them, cut them apart while warm so they cool into squares (or rectangle or triangle or whatever you've cut them into!).
df0868b8-50f2-4c0f-81c0-9298fbba4a12 Keep the oatcakes stored in an airtight container up to a week or even two, depending on the heat and humidity in your kitchen. They also freeze well (although they're so easy to make there's not a lot gained by freezing them).
9cae781e-f900-4d2a-8a50-79c2af988326 Gather the ingredients.
9cae781e-f900-4d2a-8a50-79c2af988326 In a bowl, combine the mayonnaise, Creole mustard, Creole seasoning, pepper, parsley, green onion, and bell pepper; set aside. If the Creole seasoning does not contain salt, add a dash of salt, or to taste.
9cae781e-f900-4d2a-8a50-79c2af988326 Drain the crabmeat and gently squeeze it to get as much of the liquid out as possible.
9cae781e-f900-4d2a-8a50-79c2af988326 Put the crabmeat in a medium bowl. With a spatula or wooden spoon, fold in mayonnaise mixture and 1 cup of the bread crumbs, just until blended. Shape into 8 crab cakes, about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
9cae781e-f900-4d2a-8a50-79c2af988326 I use a biscuit or cookie cutter with an open top to shape the cakes and press the ingredients down to make them hold together. Press gently into reserved crumbs. Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
9cae781e-f900-4d2a-8a50-79c2af988326 Heat the butter and oil over medium heat. When the butter stops foaming, fry crab cakes for about 5 minutes on each side, carefully turning only once. Serve with lemon wedges and Remoulade or other sauce.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Gather the ingredients.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Combine wild rice with 1/2 cup water in a small saucepan.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Bring to a simmer, then cover and simmer on low heat for 30 to 35 minutes until rice is almost tender.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Set aside.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Preheat oven to 350 F.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 In a small saucepan heat olive oil over medium heat; add onion and garlic and sauté until tender, about 5 to 7 minutes.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 In large bowl combine onion mixture, wild rice, seasoned salt, pepper, milk, and egg and combine.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Add ground beef, broken into chunks, and work gently but thoroughly with your hands to combine.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Form into meatballs about 1 inch in diameter and place on a broiler pan.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes until meatballs are no longer pink in center.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Cool and freeze, or when baked, use in your favorite recipe.
d57e3f4c-df84-44c1-87a2-5ca3f8ad5d53 Enjoy!
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Gather the ingredients.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Put the eggs in a medium saucepan and cover with water to about an inch above the eggs.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Cover the saucepan and bring to a full boil over high heat. Leaving the cover on the pan, remove from the heat and let stand for 17 minutes.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Pour out the hot water and cover with ice cold water. When the eggs are cold, peel under running water. See some tips for peeling hard-cooked eggs below.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Slice the eggs in half lengthwise and set on a platter or egg plate. Scoop the yolks into a medium bowl.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Mash the yolks with a fork, then add the mayonnaise, mustard, and salt, seasoned salt, or Creole seasoning. Add chopped fresh chives or parsley, if desired.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Taste and add freshly ground black pepper, as needed. If using salt-free seasoning, taste and add salt, as needed.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Using a small spoon or cookie scoop, fill the egg white halves with the yolk mixture.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Sprinkle the eggs lightly with paprika before serving.
1f614252-b72f-4157-97ab-7653f8263f9f Serve and enjoy!
7bd76cf6-8ef2-4cdf-8abe-eaa052b8dae7 Gather the ingredients.
7bd76cf6-8ef2-4cdf-8abe-eaa052b8dae7 Preheat the oven to 300 F.
7bd76cf6-8ef2-4cdf-8abe-eaa052b8dae7 Place the clean and dried pumpkin seeds on an ungreased cookie sheet.
7bd76cf6-8ef2-4cdf-8abe-eaa052b8dae7 Mix together the butter and Tabasco sauce and drizzle over the seeds.
7bd76cf6-8ef2-4cdf-8abe-eaa052b8dae7 Combine the cayenne pepper, cumin, chili powder, and salt and mix well; sprinkle over the coated seeds. Toss well to coat.
7bd76cf6-8ef2-4cdf-8abe-eaa052b8dae7 Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until the seeds are golden brown and crisp, stirring seeds once halfway through baking.
7bd76cf6-8ef2-4cdf-8abe-eaa052b8dae7 Cool completely, stirring occasionally. Store in airtight container.
d24b6222-9a78-4d8c-932f-6d74e342b91b Gather the ingredients.
d24b6222-9a78-4d8c-932f-6d74e342b91b Preheat oven to 425 F. Line a baking sheet with nonstick foil or parchment paper.
d24b6222-9a78-4d8c-932f-6d74e342b91b Brush cut sides of French bread with melted butter. Sprinkle lightly with onion powder and garlic powder. Top with blue cheese or Gorgonzola cheese, tomatoes, chives or green onions, mozzarella, and parsley.
d24b6222-9a78-4d8c-932f-6d74e342b91b Bake about 10 to 15 minutes, until bread is crusty on the outside and the top is melted and just beginning to turn golden.
d24b6222-9a78-4d8c-932f-6d74e342b91b Serve as is for an appetizer or serve it as an accompaniment for a classic spaghetti dinner or any other pasta dish like linguine with clam sauce.
d24b6222-9a78-4d8c-932f-6d74e342b91b Enjoy!
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Gather the ingredients.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Heat a heavy-bottomed pan on high. Add the ground beef and chorizo and brown the meat until completely cooked through. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Drain the meat from the pan and place it in a bowl. Leave some of the excess fat in the pan. Add the onion, garlic, peppers, seasoned salt, and ground black pepper to the pan and saute on medium-low heat until the vegetables are slightly softened. Do not overcook them—you want them to retain their shape and some of their texture.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Add the heavy cream, whole milk, and cream of mushroom soup to the pot. Simmer for two to three minutes.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Add the hot sauce, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sour cream, and cream cheese to the pot and stir until combined completely. It should be thick and creamy. Cook for another minute or two, then remove from the heat.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Add the mixture to a large cast iron skillet or casserole dish.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Sprinkle half of the shredded pepper jack onto the top of the casserole dish and begin arranging the tater tots on top of the casserole. You can make a pretty pattern or just cover the top of the casserole as best as you can.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Add the rest of the cheese to the top of the casserole and place it in the oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until the tater tots are golden brown and the casserole is heated through.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Top the casserole with more diced bell peppers, chopped cilantro, and sliced jalapenos if you wish to make it extra spicy.
16f5b446-4867-4f07-a429-4cccaafa2bb6 Serve and enjoy!
9c41f1ba-b25d-4ad0-844e-258c67bf40ed Gather the ingredients.
9c41f1ba-b25d-4ad0-844e-258c67bf40ed Cut the stem ends off the squash and discard them, but keep the skin and the other end intact. Using a spiralizer, shred the squash into long strands, then cut them to a manageable spaghetti-like length before you cook them. Alternatively, draw a julienne peeler down the squash, making spaghetti-like strands. You can use a peeler to make thin, broader noodle-like slices as well. The spiralizer automatically removes the core, but if you use a peeler, stop just before you reach the seedy center.
9c41f1ba-b25d-4ad0-844e-258c67bf40ed Heat the olive oil or butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the squash noodles and garlic. Cook, stirring constantly, for a few minutes or until just slightly softened. Add the basil and continue cooking for about 30 seconds to 1 minute. Add salt and pepper to taste.
9c41f1ba-b25d-4ad0-844e-258c67bf40ed Toss the squash with the Parmesan cheese and serve immediately with extra Parmesan cheese on the side for sprinkling.
2674ce25-4a5e-4ac3-8e83-b7bef13d94a6 Gather the ingredients.
2674ce25-4a5e-4ac3-8e83-b7bef13d94a6 Cook the pasta according to package directions. Before you drain the pasta, remove ⅔ cup of the pasta cooking water.
2674ce25-4a5e-4ac3-8e83-b7bef13d94a6 Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onions and sauté for 5 minutes until they are soft. Add the tomatoes and sauté for 3 more minutes until they start to soften, seasoning them with salt, pepper, and the red pepper flakes.
2674ce25-4a5e-4ac3-8e83-b7bef13d94a6 Drain the pasta, reserving the ⅔ cup of cooking water. Turn up the heat to high, add the white wine to the pan, and scrape the bottom of the pan as the wine simmers to remove any little caramelized bits that may be stuck to the bottom. Add the reserved cooking water.
2674ce25-4a5e-4ac3-8e83-b7bef13d94a6 Place the drained pasta in a serving bowl, pour the tomato mixture over, and toss to combine. Sprinkle over the fresh basil and serve hot.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Gather the ingredients.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Preheat the oven to 350 F. Combine the ground beef, sausage, and pork rinds in a large bowl. Mix until the ingredients are evenly distributed, but make sure not to over mix or else the meat will be tough.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Whisk together the egg, milk, salt, pepper, parsley, Italian seasoning, and Parmesan cheese.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Pour the egg mixture over the meat mixture. Add in the onion and garlic. Combine until all of the ingredients are evenly distributed.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Form the meat mixture into a loaf shape.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Wrap the meatloaf with the strips of bacon.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Carefully pick up the meatloaf and place it on a cooling rack over an aluminum foil-wrapped baking sheet. Pour the tomato sauce over the top of the meatloaf.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Bake in the preheated oven uncovered for one hour or until the top is caramelized and the internal temperature is 165 F. You can increase the temperature to 375 F for the last 5 minutes to further caramelize the top and crisp up the bacon.
9e080827-2b5c-4329-8b42-b0fe4b791a3a Remove from the oven and allow to cool slightly. Slice and serve immediately with your favorite keto sides, like mashed cauliflower and Brussels sprouts.
fc8bbd02-92de-47eb-829d-95b4bf902e9a Gather the ingredients.
fc8bbd02-92de-47eb-829d-95b4bf902e9a The night before cooking the prime rib, unwrap the roast and let it sit uncovered in the refrigerator. This will dry out the surface, which makes it easier to get a nice brown color on the roast.
fc8bbd02-92de-47eb-829d-95b4bf902e9a Three hours before you want to begin cooking, take the roast out of the fridge and place it on a sheet pan at room temperature.
fc8bbd02-92de-47eb-829d-95b4bf902e9a Half an hour before you start roasting, pre-heat your oven to 500 F and season the roast generously with Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper.
fc8bbd02-92de-47eb-829d-95b4bf902e9a Now it's time to do your calculation. Simply multiply the weight of your roast by five. That's your total roasting time, in minutes. For instance, if you have a 4-pound roast, 4 × 5 = 20 minutes. An 8-pound roast? 8 × 5 = 40 minutes. Remember that number.
fc8bbd02-92de-47eb-829d-95b4bf902e9a When you're ready to cook, set the roast in a roasting pan with a rack, fat-side-up. If you're nervous about the cooking time, you can insert a meat thermometer or a digital probe thermometer into the deepest part of the meat, being careful not to hit bone.
fc8bbd02-92de-47eb-829d-95b4bf902e9a Put the roast in the preheated oven and roast it for exactly however many minutes you calculated above. When the time's up, turn off the oven and walk away. Do not open the oven door for any reason for the next two hours.
fc8bbd02-92de-47eb-829d-95b4bf902e9a In two hours, take the prime rib out of the oven, carve, and serve right away. If you did use a thermometer, you'll see that the internal temperature of the meat has reached 130 F, perfect medium-rare.
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 Gather the ingredients.
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 In a large bowl, mash the beans until almost smooth with the help of a potato masher or for. Stir well with a wooden spoon once the desired texture is achieved.
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 Add 1/2 tablespoon of oil to grease the bottom of a small frying pan. Add the onions and sauté them until they are soft and translucent, about 3 to 5 minutes.
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 Combine the sautéed onions into the mashed black beans. Add the crumbled bread slices, seasoned salt, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt and pepper to taste. Mix well with a wooden spoon.
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 Once the mixture is well combined, add the flour a few tablespoons at a time. Your veggie burger mixture will be very thick, so use your hands to work the flour in well. You'll obtain a firm dough after 2 to 3 minutes of working the mixture.
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 Divide the black bean mixture into six individual patties, approximately 1/2-inch thick. Roll a handful into a ball, then gently flatten it.
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 Use the remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons of olive oil to pan-fry the burgers over medium-low heat. Allow the patties to slightly firm-up and brown on each side, about 3 minutes. If your pan is too hot, the burgers will brown too quickly and not be heated through and cooked in the middle, so adjust the heat as needed.
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 Assemble your veggie burgers with the veggies
50c72422-6ff2-45a1-b967-779b2d5663d8 Enjoy!
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 Gather the ingredients.
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 Cut the tops off of the bell peppers and rinse them under cold water; remove seeds and cut away the white ribs, which might be bitter. Chop the edible part of tops and set aside. Place the peppers in a large pot and cover with salted water.
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 Heat the olive oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat until oil is hot and the butter is foamy. Sauté the chopped bell pepper (from the tops), chopped onion, and chopped celery for about 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 Add the (undrained) canned diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, crushed garlic, oregano, basil, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook for about 10 minutes.
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 In a large mixing bowl, combine the egg with the remaining 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and Worcestershire sauce. Gently stir to blend; add ground beef, cooked rice, and 1 cup of the tomato sauce mixture. Mix well.
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 Heat the oven to 350 F.
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 Stuff the peppers loosely with the ground beef mixture and place them in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Pour the remaining tomato mixture over the stuffed peppers.
34b1b77e-e3e4-45fc-8eee-254b0917a933 Bake the peppers for about 45 minutes, or until the meat mixture is thoroughly cooked.
a2529d76-c362-4e46-8627-1496cba3718f Gather the ingredients.
a2529d76-c362-4e46-8627-1496cba3718f Set aside 2 tablespoons of butter to soften while you proceed with the recipe.
a2529d76-c362-4e46-8627-1496cba3718f Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in a medium skillet over medium heat. Add the onions, season with salt and pepper, then stir to coat with butter. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, stirring occasionally, until the onions are deep golden and very tender, about 10 minutes. If necessary, add water 1 tablespoon at a time to prevent the onions from sticking to the pan.
a2529d76-c362-4e46-8627-1496cba3718f Use the reserved softened butter to butter both sides of each slice of bread. Heat a large skillet over medium-high. Add the bread and cook until toasted underneath, about 2 minutes. Transfer to a cutting board, toasted side-up. Reserve skillet to cook the burgers.
a2529d76-c362-4e46-8627-1496cba3718f Meanwhile, shape the beef into four 5-inch round patties. Season with salt and pepper.
a2529d76-c362-4e46-8627-1496cba3718f In reserved skillet, cook burgers until browned and cooked through, 2 to 3 minutes per side for medium-rare.
a2529d76-c362-4e46-8627-1496cba3718f Top each slice of toasted bread with a slice of cheese. Place one patty over cheese, then top with some of the onions. Put the remaining bread, cheese-side down, over the onions to form a sandwich.
a2529d76-c362-4e46-8627-1496cba3718f In the same skillet, melt the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter over medium-high heat. Add the sandwiches and cook (in batches if necessary) about 2 minutes per side, or until golden brown and the cheese is melted. Flip once and repeat. Serve immediately.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad Gather ingredients.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad The night before you're going to cook, unwrap the roast and let the meat sit on a sheet pan with a rack, uncovered, in the refrigerator.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad Three hours before you're going to roast it, take the prime rib out of the fridge and let it sit at room temperature.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad Finally, 30 minutes before you start roasting, pre-heat your oven to 200 F.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad Season the meat generously with Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad For a boneless prime rib, set the roast in a roasting pan with a rack, fat-side-up. For a bone-in roast, just set the meat bone-side-down directly in the roasting pan. Insert a meat thermometer or a digital probe thermometer into the deepest part of the meat, being careful not to hit bone. If you're using a digital probe thermometer, set it to alert you when the meat hits 128 F (see note below).
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad When the oven is heated, transfer the roast to the oven and roast until the meat's internal temperature reaches 128 F, which will be another 2 1/2 to 5 hours, depending on the size of your roast.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad When the temperature hits 128 F, take the meat out of the oven and transfer it to a cutting board and cover it with foil. Leave the thermometer in!
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad As soon as you've covered the roast with foil, turn your oven up to 500 F.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad Because we roasted the prime rib at 200 F, there won't be much carryover cooking and you don't need to rest it for very long. Once you take the roast out of the oven, the temperature should rise to 130 F, which is perfect medium-rare, and within 20 minutes or so it will drop back down to 120 F.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad By which time, your oven will have fully reached 500 F. Now, put the meat back in the oven and let it roast on super-high for 6 to 10 minutes or until you have a lovely brown crust on the outside. Then take it out, carve right away.
5b8069d1-f237-409f-a573-669165ac41ad Serve and enjoy!
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Gather the ingredients.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Line a large shallow-rimmed baking pan with foil and then oil lightly. If desired, place a rack in the baking pan.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, using just enough water to moisten.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Shape into meatballs, about 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Arrange the meatballs in the pan or on the rack.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Broil the meatballs about 8 inches from the heat source for about 10 minutes.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Turn and broil for 10 minutes longer. Alternatively, the meatballs may be baked for about 30 minutes at 375 F, turning after about 15 minutes.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Put the meatballs in a large saucepan and cover with your favorite pasta sauce, homemade or store-bought.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
b61e71ff-9f9d-4c05-aba0-d28798e599e5 Serve over pasta, in a sub roll, or by itself and enjoy!
ab8df28f-c09a-4a56-980b-50ff774bd740 Gather the ingredients.
ab8df28f-c09a-4a56-980b-50ff774bd740 Place tomatoes, olive oil, lemon juice, and fresh basil in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Mix gently and set aside to marinate.
ab8df28f-c09a-4a56-980b-50ff774bd740 Bring a large pot of salted water to a fast boil and add spaghetti; cook until al dente according to package directions, about 7 to 8 minutes.
ab8df28f-c09a-4a56-980b-50ff774bd740 Drain pasta and immediately toss with the tomato mixture.
ab8df28f-c09a-4a56-980b-50ff774bd740 Serve immediately, sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 Gather the ingredients.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 The night before you are going to cook the prime rib, unwrap the roast and let it sit uncovered in the refrigerator. This will dry out the surface, which makes it easier to get a nice brown color on the roast.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 Three hours before you want to begin cooking, take the roast out of the fridge and place it on a cutting board at room temperature.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 Half an hour before you start roasting, pre-heat your oven to 450 F and season the roast generously with Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 When you're ready to cook, set the roast in a roasting pan with a rack, fat-side-up for a boneless prime rib. Or for a bone-in prime rib, skip the roasting rack and just set the roast bone-side-down in the roasting pan.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 Insert a meat thermometer or a digital probe thermometer into the deepest part of the meat, being careful not to hit bone. If you're using a digital probe thermometer, set it to alert you when the meat hits 120 F.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 Roast for 20 minutes, then lower the heat to 325 F and roast until the meat's internal temperature reaches 120 F, which will be another 1 to 3 1/2 hours, depending on the size of your roast.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 When the prime rib hits 120 F, take it out of the oven and transfer it to a cutting board and cover it with foil. Leave the thermometer in! You're going to want to rest the meat for 30 to 45 minutes, during which time the temperature will continue rising to around 130 F, which is perfect medium-rare, and then drop back down to 120 F.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 When it hits 120 F it's fully rested and ready to slice and serve.
55126462-e2a9-4b50-8fc1-c573657ffbb9 Try pairing it with a simple au jus recipe you can make while the meat is resting, or a creamy horseradish sauce. Also feel free to serve it with a variety of delicious sides.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 Gather the ingredients.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 Heat oven to 350 F. Rinse the lentils and drain.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 Fill a large soup or stockpot with water or vegetable broth and add the lentils. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat, and simmer until cooked–about 30 minutes. Don't skimp on the cooking time for these lentils because you want them to be very soft so they will mash up easily.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 Drain thoroughly then mash the lentils while they are still hot and until they are a little more than half mashed. Set aside.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 In a skillet, sauté the onions and garlic in olive oil for 3 to 5 minutes or until soft.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 In a large bowl, combine the onions, garlic, and olive oil with the mashed lentils and add the rice, salt, ketchup or barbecue sauce, sage, and Italian seasoning. Mix well.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 Gently press the entire lentil mixture into a greased loaf pan. Drizzle a bit of extra ketchup on top.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 Bake the lentil loaf for 1 hour, basting with additional ketchup every 15 minutes or so. Allow it to cool slightly before slicing and serving, as this will help the lentil loaf firm up.
81d8ecd7-4fa1-486e-a66c-4fe60e39e458 Serve and enjoy.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Gather the ingredients.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Peel about 12 to 15 large leaves off of the cabbage head.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Drop the cabbage leaves into a large pot of well salted boiling water; cover and cook for 3 minutes. Drain well.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Position a rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4).
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b For the filling, combine the ground beef, rice, onion, egg, milk, salt, and pepper in a medium bowl. Mix well and divide into 12 portions.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Place a portion of the beef mixture (about 2-1/4 oz.) onto the center of each cabbage leaf.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Roll the leaf around the filling, burrito-style, folding in the edges to seal it in.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Fasten the rolls with toothpicks. Place the rolls in a single layer in a large baking dish or an oven-safe Dutch oven.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b For the sauce, combine the diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar, and 1/2 cup of water.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Pour over the cabbage rolls. Cover with a lid or aluminum foil (carefully avoiding the toothpicks) and bake in the preheated oven for about 1 hour until the cabbage is tender and the sauce is bubbling.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Remove the rolls with a slotted spoon and discard the toothpicks.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Carefully pour the juices into a medium saucepan and place over medium heat. Stir the cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water until dissolved. Add to the sauce and bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook, whisking constantly until thickened.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Serve the cabbage rolls topped with the sauce.
76785a03-1c8f-4c05-9b5a-d865e8a2c27b Enjoy!
9c979a14-1e0a-4f4e-9ad1-c0e17eb1af46 Gather the ingredients.
9c979a14-1e0a-4f4e-9ad1-c0e17eb1af46 Sift the flour to bring in more air and combine with sugar, baking powder, and salt in a large bowl until well mixed.
9c979a14-1e0a-4f4e-9ad1-c0e17eb1af46 Mix in the soy milk or milk substitute of choice and oil and beat together until batter is smooth. If choosing to use the apple cider vinegar tablespoon remember to remove one tablespoon of the milk substitute before adding it to the mix to avoid a runny batter.
9c979a14-1e0a-4f4e-9ad1-c0e17eb1af46 Drop 1/4 cup of batter at a time onto a hot oiled griddle or a well greased frying pan over medium-high heat.
9c979a14-1e0a-4f4e-9ad1-c0e17eb1af46 When bubbles appear on the surface of the pancake, approximately 3 minutes, flip and cook the other side for another 2 minutes.​
9c979a14-1e0a-4f4e-9ad1-c0e17eb1af46 Serve with your favorite toppings and enjoy!
edc8e20a-eaa1-4f79-9f0a-e1c8f9696581 Gather the ingredients.
edc8e20a-eaa1-4f79-9f0a-e1c8f9696581 About 30 minutes before you plan to start roasting, take the pork loin out of the fridge and let it sit at room temperature.
edc8e20a-eaa1-4f79-9f0a-e1c8f9696581 Preheat the oven to 450 F.
edc8e20a-eaa1-4f79-9f0a-e1c8f9696581 In a small bowl, combine the oil, garlic, salt, pepper, sage, rosemary, and thyme, and mix until a paste forms.
edc8e20a-eaa1-4f79-9f0a-e1c8f9696581 Dry the pork loin with paper towels and rub it all over with the seasoning paste. Set it on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Insert an oven-safe meat thermometer into the very center of the roast on a slight angle. If you're using a digital thermometer with a temperature alert function, set it to 135 F. Transfer the pork to the oven.
edc8e20a-eaa1-4f79-9f0a-e1c8f9696581 Roast for 15 minutes, then turn the oven temperature down to 300 F. Let the loin continue roasting for another 40 to 60 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 135 F.
edc8e20a-eaa1-4f79-9f0a-e1c8f9696581 Take the roast out of the oven and cover it with foil. Let it rest for 10 to 15 minutes; during this time, the roast's internal temperature will increase to around 140 F, which means it is ready to slice.
edc8e20a-eaa1-4f79-9f0a-e1c8f9696581 Serve and enjoy.
cf2b0775-9ec4-4a02-a351-487593f712fd Gather the ingredients.
cf2b0775-9ec4-4a02-a351-487593f712fd Toast two slices of bread in the toaster until they are lightly toasted.
cf2b0775-9ec4-4a02-a351-487593f712fd Remove the toast from the toaster, and top one slice of bread with the thick slices of fresh tomato. Then, sprinkle the dash of salt and ground black pepper over the tomatoes.
cf2b0775-9ec4-4a02-a351-487593f712fd Place the avocado slices on the second slice of toast and use a knife to gently spread the avocado on the bread. Then place this slice of toast, avocado side down, on the tomato sandwich.
cf2b0775-9ec4-4a02-a351-487593f712fd Slice the sandwich in half, if you desire, and serve immediately. This sandwich is delicious on its own but if you're looking for something crunchy on the side, you can't go wrong with carrot sticks. Leave the chips for your splurge day.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Gather the ingredients.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Peel the potatoes and cut them into 2-inch cubes. Put the potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with water. Add 2 teaspoons of salt to the water.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Place the saucepan over high heat and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cover the pan. Continue cooking for about 20 to 25 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Meanwhile, just before the potatoes are done, heat the milk in a small saucepan over medium-low heat until hot. Set aside.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Drain the potatoes and place the pan over the heat for about 20 to 30 seconds longer, or just long enough to dry the potatoes. Remove the potatoes from the heat.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Break the potatoes up with a potato masher. Alternatively, for a smoother texture, put them through a potato ricer first.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Add the warmed milk, melted butter, and black pepper.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Continue mashing until smooth, adding salt, to taste, and more milk, as needed.
3bbd6780-83bf-4eaf-8f43-07fd5f08e880 Transfer the potatoes to a serving bowl and serve immediately.
527f78d9-3573-4648-b361-6c1d2681a5c9 Place the walnuts on a cookie sheet and toast in a preheated oven at 350 F for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove, let cool and roughly chop.
527f78d9-3573-4648-b361-6c1d2681a5c9 In a large bowl, toss together all the ingredients.
527f78d9-3573-4648-b361-6c1d2681a5c9 Serve plain or on a bed of romaine lettuce or mixed greens.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f Gather the ingredients.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f Peel the potatoes. Cut generous 1/2-inch slices, then cut again into fries the same width. Place the cut potatoes into a colander and rinse under cold running water until the water runs clear.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f Bring a large pot of water to a boil, add the fries, and cook for 4 minutes. Drain, then spread them onto either a clean kitchen towel or paper. Pat to dry thoroughly and leave to cool completely.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f In a large pot, melt the duck fat and heat to 375 F. If you don’t have a thermometer, the fat is hot enough when you drop in one fry and it sizzles and floats to the surface.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f While the fat heats up, line a large roasting tin with paper towels and have a slotted spoon on hand.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f Put only enough fries into the hot oil to form a single layer. Once they are in, turn the heat up slightly to maintain 375 F as the temperature will drop slightly. Let the fries sizzle and rise back the surface, then cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring from time to time, until they are starting to brown. Scoop them up with the slotted spoon and lay onto the paper towels to drain.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f Wait for the temperature of the fat to rise again and add another layer and repeat. Continue until you have partially cooked all the fries. At this point, you can keep the fries to finish off when ready to serve by covering with a tea towel and popping the tray into the refrigerator.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f Once you are ready to serve, reheat the fat as before and prepare another dish with a kitchen towel. This time, you can add more fries than before, but not so many that the pan is crowded. The fries will crisp up and turn golden within minutes, so keep an eye on them. As soon as they look like they are going from golden to dark, whip them out and drain on paper towels. Keep warm in the oven until you have cooked the rest.
197dbf3d-e285-4735-933f-f9dd8fc0878f Serve immediately sprinkled with a little salt. Enjoy.
b9bc2b84-960d-43d8-a310-a79baa1c0cfd Gather the ingredients.
b9bc2b84-960d-43d8-a310-a79baa1c0cfd First, in a large saucepan, heat the vegetable oil over medium heat. Next, add the cucumbers, garlic, and onions to the pan and heat just until the onions are transparent, about 6 minutes.
b9bc2b84-960d-43d8-a310-a79baa1c0cfd Next, add the vegetable broth to the pan, and simmer until the cucumber is fully soft, about 15 to 20 minutes.
b9bc2b84-960d-43d8-a310-a79baa1c0cfd Remove the pan from the heat. Carefully transfer the mixture to a blender or food processor and then carefully blend just until the mixture is completely smooth. While the mixture is still warm, stir in the fresh dill and season with fresh ground black pepper, to taste.
b9bc2b84-960d-43d8-a310-a79baa1c0cfd Place the entire mixture in the refrigerator and allow to chill until fully cool.
b9bc2b84-960d-43d8-a310-a79baa1c0cfd Stir in the soy milk just before serving. Taste, and adjust seasonings to taste.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Gather the ingredients.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Cut the potatoes into 3/4-inch sticks. Leave the skins on for a more rustic look as well as saving time. If you don’t like the skins, you can peel them.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Place the potatoes in a large bowl immediately after cutting. Cover them with cold water and soak them for at least 30 minutes or up to 12 hours. If you're soaking for a longer period, make sure to cover them with plastic wrap and place them in the refrigerator.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Drain the potatoes and place them on a tray lined with paper towels. Pat them completely dry. Toss the cornstarch, paprika, salt, and black pepper in a small bowl.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Add the potatoes to a large bowl. Drizzle olive oil over the top and then toss them to completely coat.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Sprinkle the cornstarch mixture over the top of the potatoes and toss them to coat.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Add the French fries to the basket of the air fryer. Fry at 360 F for 25 to 30 minutes, pausing the air fryer to toss the fries every 5 minutes.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Increase the temperature to 425 F and cook for another 5 minutes until they are golden brown and crisp.
5d446000-41ce-4cb1-b19c-722ee231028a Serve the fries alongside ketchup or your favorite dipping sauce. Sprinkle on more salt if you wish or top with chopped parsley or chives.
5deeebf9-8635-4db1-9840-66189d6df44e Gather the ingredients.
5deeebf9-8635-4db1-9840-66189d6df44e Prepare a gas or charcoal grill to medium heat: You should be able to hold your hand about an inch above the cooking grate for 3 to 4 seconds before pulling it away from the heat. If you are also using the grill to cook something else that requires more heat, place the peaches around the edges; they're cooler. Or cook dinner, let the fire cool down, and then grill the peaches.
5deeebf9-8635-4db1-9840-66189d6df44e Cut the peaches in half and pit them.
5deeebf9-8635-4db1-9840-66189d6df44e If you want to add cinnamon and/or sugar, grill entire peach halves; otherwise, you can cut them into wedges, if you like. Peeling the peaches isn't necessary for the grill, but if you want to, you can.
5deeebf9-8635-4db1-9840-66189d6df44e Lightly brush the peaches with the oil, being particularly aware of coating the cut sides well.
5deeebf9-8635-4db1-9840-66189d6df44e Set the oiled peaches on the medium hot grill. Make sure they aren't touching so the hot air of the grill can circulate around each piece.
5deeebf9-8635-4db1-9840-66189d6df44e Cook the peaches until grill marks form, turning as necessary to mark all cut sides for the best presentation. Turn the peach halves over, sprinkle with the cinnamon and sugar, if using. Cook until the peaches are tender, but not falling apart, about 8 minutes total.
5deeebf9-8635-4db1-9840-66189d6df44e Serve grilled peaches hot, warm, or even at room temperature. Enjoy!
b0e562ea-d292-48b2-8315-618180098097 Preheat an oven to 450 F. Trim off and discard the stem and root ends of the rutabaga. Peel the rutabaga.
b0e562ea-d292-48b2-8315-618180098097 Use a sharp knife or a kitchen mandoline, if you have one, and cut the rutabaga into evenly sized sticks or fries. If using a knife, first cut the rutabaga in half, then cut each half into even 1/4-inch thick slices. Stack the slices and cut them the other direction into 1/4-inch thick sticks. Repeat with the remaining half of the rutabaga. If using a mandoline, set it up for wide julienne and push the rutabaga through—note that rutabagas have a fairly thick or dense texture, and it can take some force to get them through the julienne setting on mandolines.
b0e562ea-d292-48b2-8315-618180098097 Put the rutabaga sticks in a large bowl and drizzle with the oil. Toss the sticks so they are thoroughly and evenly coated with the oil. Sprinkle with the pepper and/or garlic powder, if using them, and toss to distribute them evenly over the rutabaga.
b0e562ea-d292-48b2-8315-618180098097 Spread the rutabaga sticks in a single layer on a lightly oiled baking sheet or a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Sprinkle the sticks evenly with the salt.
b0e562ea-d292-48b2-8315-618180098097 Bake the rutabaga sticks for 20 minutes. Remove the pan from the oven and turn over the rutabaga sticks. Return to the oven and bake until they are tender and well browned, about 40 minutes.
b0e562ea-d292-48b2-8315-618180098097 If the rutabaga sticks towards the edges are more browned earlier, you can take them off the pan and return the rest to brown all the way. The appeal of these baked fries is the contrast between the crispy edges and the sweet tender centers, so don't skimp on the cooking time.
b0e562ea-d292-48b2-8315-618180098097 Serve the fries hot.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Gather the ingredients.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Cut each onion in half and then thinly slice.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Heat the olive oil and butter in a medium-sized sauté pan over medium-low heat. Add the onions to the pan and spread them evenly. Sprinkle salt over the onions.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Stir the onions every few minutes until they are caramel-colored, fragrant and completely soft, about 30 minutes. Set the onions aside and begin the pasta.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Cook the orecchiette according to package directions, leaving the pasta al dente. Set the pasta aside and make the cheese sauce.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Add the butter to a large pot over medium heat. Once the butter has melted, whisk in the flour. Cook the butter and flour mixture for about 3 minutes, stirring frequently, to cook off the flour taste.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Add the milk and whisk until combined. Heat the milk mixture until it is hot, but not boiling.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Slowly add in the cheeses and whisk until they are melted. Add the salt and pepper and stir. Take off of the heat.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Add the breadcrumbs to the melted butter and stir to combine.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Butter a 9x13-inch casserole dish and add the prepared macaroni and cheese mixture.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Top the macaroni and cheese with the caramelized onions. Cover the top with the buttered breadcrumbs and place in the oven on a center rack.
cf0413e1-3a40-4a21-a456-22752a51f486 Bake for about 20 minutes, until the top is golden brown and the edges are bubbly.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 200 F.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Cut off both ends of the onions and peel off the skin.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Slice the onions into thick rings.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Carefully separate the rings from each other. Set aside the innermost rings for another recipe. If the rings break, you can still use them.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Prepare the 3 dredging bowls. Put the flour in 1 shallow bowl. Beat the eggs and milk in another shallow bowl. Add the panko breadcrumbs to a third shallow bowl. In a separate small bowl, mix the smoked paprika, onion powder, garlic powder, and salt, then divide the mixture evenly among each of the bowls. Whisk each bowl to disperse the seasonings.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Dip the onion rings in the flour first. Completely coat both sides of the rings and the inner portion.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Dip the flour-coated rings into the egg mixture. Make sure to completely coat them with the egg so you cannot see any of the flour. You may need to flip the rings a few times.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Dip the rings in the breadcrumb mixture. To thoroughly coat them, use your fingers to press the breadcrumbs onto the rings.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Generously spray the inside of the air fryer with cooking spray. Carefully place a single layer of the onion rings into the air fryer and spray the tops with cooking spray. Cook on 375 F for 10 minutes, flipping each ring halfway through the cooking time.
eddd9d4a-0bca-49df-8f1f-1f4757358a1e Transfer the first batch to a baking sheet and place in the oven to keep warm. Cook the second batch of rings. Serve with creamy dipping sauces, honey mustard, or ketchup if desired.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Gather the ingredients.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 In a large bowl, dissolve the 2 tablespoons of salt in 1 cup warm water; stir until the salt is fully dissolved. Add 6 to 8 cups cold water. Set the brine aside.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Cut off and discard the stem end of the eggplant.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Cut the eggplant into 3/4-inch thick slices (either diagonal, crosswise, or lengthwise).
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Place the slices in the saltwater brine.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Weigh the eggplant slices down with an upside-down plate; let soak for at least 30 minutes or up to an hour.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Meanwhile, heat a charcoal or gas grill to medium-high heat. You should be able to hold your hand about an inch above the cooking grate for 3 to 4 seconds before pulling it away from the heat.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Drain the eggplant and pat it dry with paper towels or a clean kitchen towel.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Lay the slices on a large baking sheet or tray. Brush one side with olive oil and sprinkle with salt.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Place the slices with the oiled side on the grill. Close the lid if using a gas or electric grill and cook until grill marks appear; about 5 minutes.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Brush the top sides of the slices with oil and sprinkle them with salt. Turn the slices over, close the lid of the grill, and cook until grill marks appear on the other side and the eggplant is very tender; about 5 more minutes.
f43038dc-fcfc-4ebf-a682-5c38ff3e2594 Serve hot or at room temperature.
8a61d287-1381-4063-b775-48d0a60eba65 Remove stem and blossom ends of squash and cut them into large chunks. Place in a large saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat to low, cover the pan, and cook until squash is very tender, about 10 to 15 minutes. Drain thoroughly.
8a61d287-1381-4063-b775-48d0a60eba65 In a large bowl, mash the drained squash. Add the remaining ingredients to the mashed squash and blend well.
8a61d287-1381-4063-b775-48d0a60eba65 Cover the bowl and refrigerate the batter for a few hours or fry them right away.
8a61d287-1381-4063-b775-48d0a60eba65 Heat about two inches of oil in a deep saucepan or deep fryer to 370 F.
8a61d287-1381-4063-b775-48d0a60eba65 Drop squash batter by spoonfuls into the hot oil.
8a61d287-1381-4063-b775-48d0a60eba65 Cook the squash fritters until they are golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes, turning them as they fry to brown all sides.
8a61d287-1381-4063-b775-48d0a60eba65 Remove with a metal slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
8a61d287-1381-4063-b775-48d0a60eba65 Serve hot with Sriracha mayonnaise (see below) or another dipping sauce.
86b6eb8b-1d23-42c4-9e6a-ae8f8b9caa69 Gather the ingredients.
86b6eb8b-1d23-42c4-9e6a-ae8f8b9caa69 Heat the oven to 400 F.
86b6eb8b-1d23-42c4-9e6a-ae8f8b9caa69 Toss the squash, shallot, thyme, olive oil, and salt together in a bowl.
86b6eb8b-1d23-42c4-9e6a-ae8f8b9caa69 Spread the mixture out onto a sheet pan. Bake 15 to 25 minutes or until the squash is tender. Monitor it periodically by testing it with a fork.
86b6eb8b-1d23-42c4-9e6a-ae8f8b9caa69 Serve hot or at room temperature. Enjoy.
c078918c-7d17-46cf-8f20-2c456d6e0aa8 Gather the ingredients.
c078918c-7d17-46cf-8f20-2c456d6e0aa8 Trim and chop the zucchini, getting rid of the ends. Reserve.
c078918c-7d17-46cf-8f20-2c456d6e0aa8 Heat a medium pot over medium-high heat and add oil, onions, and salt. Cook onions, stirring occasionally until translucent and tender, for about 5 minutes.
c078918c-7d17-46cf-8f20-2c456d6e0aa8 Add zucchini and broth to the onions. Set the heat to high to bring to a boil. Reduce the heat immediately after boiling and maintain a steady simmer until zucchini is very tender, for about 15 minutes.
c078918c-7d17-46cf-8f20-2c456d6e0aa8 Once the zucchini is cooked, turn off the heat. To avoid burns, let the soup cool for at least 20 minutes before blending. Working in batches if necessary, blend soup on high speed until very smooth.
c078918c-7d17-46cf-8f20-2c456d6e0aa8 Transfer pureed soup to a large bowl or sealable container. Cover and chill until cold, for at least 1 hour.
c078918c-7d17-46cf-8f20-2c456d6e0aa8 When ready to serve, stir with cream or yogurt, if using, and add salt and pepper to taste.
c078918c-7d17-46cf-8f20-2c456d6e0aa8 Decorate with fresh cilantro and enjoy!
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 Gather the ingredients and preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 Grease a 2 1/2- to 3-quart casserole dish.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 Cook the spaghetti in boiling salted water following the package directions. Drain well.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 In a large bowl, combine the cooked and drained spaghetti with 1 cup of cheddar cheese and 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 Add the diced turkey and pimientos.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 In a skillet or saute pan, melt butter and saute the mushrooms and onions until they are tender and most of the liquid has evaporated; add to the turkey mixture along with remaining ingredients. Taste and add salt and pepper, as needed. Gently stir to combine ingredients.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 Transfer the mixture to the prepared casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheddar and Parmesan cheeses.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 Cover the baking dish with a lid or foil and bake for about 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 If desired, place the casserole under the broiler (high heat) for about 4 to 6 minutes, or until the top is lightly browned.
1525d0bf-8f73-4064-b706-a9851c0a53d0 Serve and enjoy!
3ccbc9f1-45a8-426f-a7b9-b3d2fb01e4b5 Gather the ingredients.
3ccbc9f1-45a8-426f-a7b9-b3d2fb01e4b5 Warm the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add the garlic and sauté for 1 minute.
3ccbc9f1-45a8-426f-a7b9-b3d2fb01e4b5 Add the broccoli florets. Cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
3ccbc9f1-45a8-426f-a7b9-b3d2fb01e4b5 Add 2 tablespoons water, then cover the pan and steam the broccoli for about 2 minutes until it becomes bright green and the water has evaporated.
3ccbc9f1-45a8-426f-a7b9-b3d2fb01e4b5 Add the tomatoes and cook for 1 additional minute.
3ccbc9f1-45a8-426f-a7b9-b3d2fb01e4b5 Add the herbs and salt to taste.
3ccbc9f1-45a8-426f-a7b9-b3d2fb01e4b5 Stir gently and serve.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Gather the ingredients.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Combine the flour and salt in a large shallow bowl or on a clean work surface. Make a well in the center, almost like a "bowl" of flour, to hold the eggs. Crack the eggs into it.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Use a fork to beat the eggs and then gradually start incorporating the flour into the eggs (as you beat them, they will slowly but surely take up some flour from along the edge of where the eggs meet the flour).
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Keep stirring and pulling in more flour until a solid dough forms. The dough will be sticky. Don't worry, you'll be working in more flour in a moment. Add too much flour now and the extra flour needed to roll out the noodles will lead to a dry rather than tender noodle in the end.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Turn the dough out onto a well-floured work surface. With well-floured hands, knead the dough, incorporating more flour as necessary to keep it from sticking to either the work surface or your hands, until the dough is smooth and firm and no longer sticky.
