This takes roughly 5 to 10 minutes.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Wrap the dough with plastic wrap and chill it for at least 30 minutes and up to overnight.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Divide the chilled dough into 2 pieces and work with one half of the dough at a time.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 On a well-floured surface, roll out the dough to the desired thickness (anywhere from 1/4 inch to paper thin, depending on your preference). Be sure to rotate, or otherwise move the dough, between each pass of the rolling pin to keep the dough from sticking to the work surface underneath. Sprinkle everything with flour—including lifting the dough and flouring the work surface again—as necessary to keep the dough from sticking.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Use a sharp knife or pizza cutting wheel to cut the noodles. You can make them as narrow or wide as you like but cut them as evenly as possible to ensure a uniform cooking time. If you fold the dough to cut, make sure it is floured so it does not stick together.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Lay the noodles on a cooling or drying rack and let them sit until ready to cook. Repeat rolling and cutting with the remaining half of the dough.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Boil the noodles in well-salted water until tender to the bite (2 to 10 minutes for fresh noodles depending on the thickness). Drain and serve.
ebfe69fb-17e1-4f27-9717-5f04b6d14ab0 Enjoy.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 Slice off the stem and lower ends of the cucumbers and compost or discard them. Slice the cucumbers lengthwise. Scoop out the seeds with a small spoon.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 Chop the cucumbers very finely, or pulse a few times in a food processor. You should have about 4 cups of finely chopped cucumber. Transfer to a large, non-reactive bowl.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 Peel the onion and slice off the ends. Slice off the stem ends of the bell pepper and remove the seeds. Finely chop the onion and bell pepper, or pulse a few times in a food processor. The vegetables should be in tiny pieces, but not totally pulverized into a purée. You should have about 1 1/2 cups of finely chopped onion and bell pepper. Add to the cucumber in the bowl.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 Add 2 tablespoons of kosher salt to the vegetables and mix well. If that seems like a lot of salt, don't worry: You'll rinse most of it off later. The salt is there to draw water out of the vegetables, a step that results in better texture and flavor in the finished relish.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 Cover the bowl of vegetables and leave it in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 Transfer the vegetables to a finely meshed sieve or strainer and let them drain for a couple of minutes. Rinse them well with cool water and let drain again. Get out even more of the liquid by squeezing with your clean hands (squeeze hard), or by pressing the vegetables against the sieve with the back of a wooden spoon.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 In a medium saucepan, whisk the cornstarch or ClearJel into the cool or room temperature vinegar. Stir in the sugar and spices. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often to help dissolve the sugar and prevent lumps.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 Once the syrup is boiling and becoming translucent, add the vegetables. Simmer the relish for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
abd1d995-8fb7-40b4-b304-370d38e86786 Scoop the hot dog relish into clean, hot canning jars leaving 1/2-inch of head-space. It is not necessary to sterilize the jars for this recipe. Screw on canning lids. Process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes. Once the jars are processed and sealed, sweet relish will keep at room temperature for up to 1 year. It is still safe to eat after that, but the quality will decline. Once opened, store the jars in the refrigerator.
ec3b1d07-0497-42cf-85c9-63251c533dc3 Gather the ingredients.
ec3b1d07-0497-42cf-85c9-63251c533dc3 Add the carrots, onions, ginger, and curry powder to a soup pot and cover with the vegetable broth. Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, until carrots are soft.
ec3b1d07-0497-42cf-85c9-63251c533dc3 Allow to cool slightly, and then puree in a blender, working in batches if needed.
ec3b1d07-0497-42cf-85c9-63251c533dc3 Return to the heat and stir in coconut milk until well combined.
ec3b1d07-0497-42cf-85c9-63251c533dc3 Season generously with sea salt, to taste.
ec3b1d07-0497-42cf-85c9-63251c533dc3 Serve hot or chill until cold. This carrot soup will thicken as it cools, so if eating this vegan carrot soup cold, you may want to add a bit extra liquid before serving.
d30d0e43-37a5-43e7-bdf9-d450080155df Gather the ingredients.
d30d0e43-37a5-43e7-bdf9-d450080155df Heat oven to 350 F.
d30d0e43-37a5-43e7-bdf9-d450080155df Spray a 2 1/2- to 3-quart casserole dish with cooking spray.
d30d0e43-37a5-43e7-bdf9-d450080155df Combine the noodles, soup, peas, cheese, tuna, and milk. Add salt and freshly ground black pepper. Spoon into the prepared baking dish.
d30d0e43-37a5-43e7-bdf9-d450080155df In a small bowl, toss the breadcrumbs with the melted butter and sprinkle over the top of the casserole.
d30d0e43-37a5-43e7-bdf9-d450080155df Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until hot and bubbly and the breadcrumbs are browned.
d30d0e43-37a5-43e7-bdf9-d450080155df Serve and enjoy.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Gather the ingredients.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Wash and dry the oranges. Using a sharp vegetable peeler or paring knife, remove the brightly colored zest—and only the brightly colored zest—from the oranges. Be sure to leave behind any and all of the white pith directly underneath as it is very bitter.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Chop the zest. Bigger pieces for chunkier marmalade, ribbon-like strips for a more spreadable result. Set the zest aside.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Cut the ends off the zested oranges and then, working with one orange at a time, cut off the thick white pith from around each orange.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Working over a bowl to catch the juices, hold a fully peeled orange and use a sharp knife to cut out each segment from the membrane holding the sections together.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Squeeze any juice out of the membranes once you've cut out all the fruit. Set the membrane aside, along with any seeds—the pectin in these will help "set" the marmalade later. Discard the ends and white pith.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Combine the zest, fruit, juice, sugar, and water in a large heavy pot and bring to a boil. Stir just until the sugar dissolves and stop stirring.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Meanwhile, lay a double layer of cheesecloth in a medium bowl and put the membranes and seeds on top. Lift up the corners and tie the cheesecloth into a bag to hold the membranes and seeds.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Add this "pectin bag" to the pot. Bring the mixture tso a boil, and place a couple of small plates in the freezer to chill them.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Meanwhile, bring the marmalade to 220 F and hold it there for 5 minutes. Be patient, this can take quite a while. Do not stir.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Put a dollop of the mixture on a chilled plate. Swirl the plate to spread the mixture a bit and drag a spoon through the mixture. If your marmalade is set, your spoon will leave a trail, and you'll still be able to see the plate where you dragged the spoon.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Remove the pectin bag, squeezing any marmalade out and back into the pot, and discard the bag. Take the marmalade off the heat and let sit for 5 minutes. Set up clean jars (if canning, they should be hot and sterilized) next to the pot.
89b95075-dc13-4c47-9c95-7089cebd227f Stir the marmalade to distribute the zest evenly in the mixture. Use a ladle to transfer the marmalade into the jars, leaving 1/2 inch of headspace at the top of each jar. Put the lids on the jars, and refrigerate. Marmalade will last for up to 4 weeks. Or, you can proceed with canning, as directed below.
9b1287e6-1c75-48e0-9dcb-48dc8a9d956e Gather the ingredients.
9b1287e6-1c75-48e0-9dcb-48dc8a9d956e Bring the water to boil in a medium saucepan. Add the salt and butter and allow the butter to melt.
9b1287e6-1c75-48e0-9dcb-48dc8a9d956e When the water has returned to a boil, stir in the rice. Let the water return to a light simmer.
9b1287e6-1c75-48e0-9dcb-48dc8a9d956e Stir again, cover the pot, and turn the heat down to low. Keep the rice simmering slightly, and keep the pot covered (you may have to peek after a few minutes to make sure the heat is at the correct temperature, but then let it cook, covered).
9b1287e6-1c75-48e0-9dcb-48dc8a9d956e Start checking to see if the rice is tender and all of the liquid is absorbed in about 17 minutes. It may take up to 25, especially if you are making a larger quantity of rice.
9b1287e6-1c75-48e0-9dcb-48dc8a9d956e When the rice is cooked, turn off the heat and let it sit for another couple of minutes to finish absorbing any liquid.
9b1287e6-1c75-48e0-9dcb-48dc8a9d956e Take off the lid, fluff the rice with a fork, and let it sit for another 2 minutes so that some of the excess moisture in the rice dries off.
9b1287e6-1c75-48e0-9dcb-48dc8a9d956e Serve with your side of protein and enjoy!
e63679e0-ea04-44c2-866a-3e6b843236ff To prepare the round zucchini, first cut off any of the remaining stem. Then cut it into quarters, do so from the top so that it resembles something like apple wedges. Each of the four quarters should now be sliced into even-sized pieces. Prepare the remaining ingredients.
e63679e0-ea04-44c2-866a-3e6b843236ff Heat the olive oil in a large pan. Once the oil is hot add the onion and sauté it until soft and translucent. Next add the chiles, zucchini pieces, minced garlic, and dried epazote if using. Sprinkle a little bit of fine sea salt over the vegetables and sauté until the chiles and zucchini have softened to your liking. Taste and if necessary add a bit more salt. Serve.
2850bcd7-fc8d-4277-981b-fe58fd93350b Heat the oven to 400 F / 200 C / Gas 6.
2850bcd7-fc8d-4277-981b-fe58fd93350b Slice the ends off of the sprouts and remove loose, discolored, or damaged leaves from the outside. Cut each sprout in half lengthwise and put them in a large bowl.
2850bcd7-fc8d-4277-981b-fe58fd93350b In a small saucepan over medium-low heat, heat the olive oil. Add the sliced garlic, lower the heat, and cook for about 4 to 5 minutes. Don't let the garlic brown or burn. It should be gently bubbling around the garlic pieces. Remove the garlic with a slotted spoon and discard.
2850bcd7-fc8d-4277-981b-fe58fd93350b Pour the olive oil over the sprouts and sprinkle with the garlic powder, about 1/4 teaspoon of kosher salt, and 1/4 teaspoon of freshly ground black pepper. Toss to coat the sprouts with the oil and seasonings.
2850bcd7-fc8d-4277-981b-fe58fd93350b Arrange the sprouts in a single layer in a large rimmed baking pan, such as a half-sheet pan.
2850bcd7-fc8d-4277-981b-fe58fd93350b Roast for about 20 minutes, shaking the pan a few times. Turn the sprouts and continue roasting for about 10 to 15 minutes, until they are tender and browned on the outside.
2850bcd7-fc8d-4277-981b-fe58fd93350b Remove from the oven and transfer to a serving dish. Sprinkle with more kosher salt for serving, if desired.
92c10bb8-0d4f-4c15-858b-ca9a2f8f156e Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F.
92c10bb8-0d4f-4c15-858b-ca9a2f8f156e Combine everything in a large bowl.
92c10bb8-0d4f-4c15-858b-ca9a2f8f156e Spoon the mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
92c10bb8-0d4f-4c15-858b-ca9a2f8f156e Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.
92c10bb8-0d4f-4c15-858b-ca9a2f8f156e Serve and enjoy!
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 In a bowl, whisk the milk with the egg and vanilla extract.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 To the bread machine pan in the order suggested by your machine's manufacturer, add the milk mixture, flour, sugar, salt, butter, and yeast.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 Start the machine on the dough cycle. Add the blueberries and ground cinnamon at the beep.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 Grease a 9-inch round baking pan.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 Turn the dough out onto a floured surface and punch it down. Knead a few times, adding a bit more flour, if needed, to keep it from sticking to the surface and hands.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 Shape the dough into 16 uniform balls and place them side-by-side in the prepared round pan. Cover the pan with a kitchen towel and let the rolls rise in a draft-free place for 40 minutes.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 Heat the oven to 350 F.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 In a small bowl, whisk the water and egg yolk. Brush the mixture over the tops of the rolls.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 Bake, the rolls for 20 to 25 minutes, or until the tops, are golden brown.
12c58058-c335-4845-a83b-59ff141224b0 Remove the rolls to a rack and let them cool for 5 to 10 minutes while you prepare the icing.
7db6c9a3-b9bf-4fb3-a560-d035c60db4a7 Gather the ingredients.
7db6c9a3-b9bf-4fb3-a560-d035c60db4a7 Combine the carrots, potatoes, onion, garlic, water, olive oil, salt, and pepper in a 3 to 4-quart crockpot and stir to combine.
7db6c9a3-b9bf-4fb3-a560-d035c60db4a7 Cover the crockpot and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or until vegetables are tender when pierced with a fork.
7db6c9a3-b9bf-4fb3-a560-d035c60db4a7 Serve and enjoy!
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Gather the ingredients.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Peel, de-stem, or remove seeds from the fruit, as appropriate.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Place the fruit, water, and sugar into a pot.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Cook the fruit with the sugar and water, bringing it to a boil and then lowering the heat to simmer.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Smash the fruit while it is cooking.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Simmer until the mixture has thickened to a syrupy consistency. This should take about 10 minutes.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Once the mixture has thickened, you can press it through a strainer to make a thin syrup.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b If you prefer a thicker syrup, process the cooked syrup in a food processor.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Serve with your favorite breakfast item.
3e5ed8fd-9047-403b-8e6c-5db582ea4d5b Enjoy!
317d3b08-7b06-4c73-a910-9014b791f602 In a small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar or lemon juice, garlic (if using), and salt.
317d3b08-7b06-4c73-a910-9014b791f602 Shuck the corn and cut off kernels. To help keep the kernels from escaping, cut over a large bowl.
317d3b08-7b06-4c73-a910-9014b791f602 Peel the cucumbers and cut them in half lengthwise. Use a spoon to scrape out and discard the watery seeds in the center. Dice the cucumbers fairly small and add them to bowl.
317d3b08-7b06-4c73-a910-9014b791f602 Core or hull the tomatoes, cutting out the stiff bit at the top where they attached to the vine. Cut the tomatoes in half crosswise (if the tomato were a globe, cut it along the equator). Gently squeeze out any of the watery seeds that come out easily. Dice the tomatoes and add them to the bowl.
317d3b08-7b06-4c73-a910-9014b791f602 Cut off the stem end of the onion and cut it in half lengthwise. Remove and discard the peel. Hold onto the end to keep the onion halves steady as you dice the onion. To mitigate the pungent flavor of the onion, feel free to put the onion in a strainer and rinse it with cool water. Drain completely. Spread the diced onion on layers of paper towels to dry before adding to the bowl.
317d3b08-7b06-4c73-a910-9014b791f602 Toss the vegetables with the dressing well. For an extra burst of flavor, add minced fresh herbs on top before serving.
317d3b08-7b06-4c73-a910-9014b791f602 Serve immediately or store in the fridge. Toss again before serving.
8dacc957-9f34-4599-acd7-baf0d7e59eb8 Gather the ingredients.
8dacc957-9f34-4599-acd7-baf0d7e59eb8 Heat the oven to 350 F/177 C/Gas 4.
8dacc957-9f34-4599-acd7-baf0d7e59eb8 Mix the soup, milk, and pepper in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
8dacc957-9f34-4599-acd7-baf0d7e59eb8 Add the green beans and 2/3 cup of the French fried onions.
8dacc957-9f34-4599-acd7-baf0d7e59eb8 Stir together the mixture.
8dacc957-9f34-4599-acd7-baf0d7e59eb8 Bake the casserole for about 25 minutes or until bubbly around the edges.
8dacc957-9f34-4599-acd7-baf0d7e59eb8 Top with the remaining 2/3 cup of fried onions and bake about 5 more minutes or until the onions are lightly browned.
8dacc957-9f34-4599-acd7-baf0d7e59eb8 Serve and enjoy!
9dae8112-7ae3-4c0e-a2c7-80d7bfcb0431 Gather the ingredients.
9dae8112-7ae3-4c0e-a2c7-80d7bfcb0431 Trim tough root ends from asparagus spears, then cut into 2-inch lengths. Place in a microwave-safe bowl with a lid.
9dae8112-7ae3-4c0e-a2c7-80d7bfcb0431 Sprinkle asparagus with kosher salt, onion powder, and garlic powder.
9dae8112-7ae3-4c0e-a2c7-80d7bfcb0431 Pour in lemon juice and dot with butter.
9dae8112-7ae3-4c0e-a2c7-80d7bfcb0431 Cover with lid and microwave on high power for 2 to 3 minutes.
9dae8112-7ae3-4c0e-a2c7-80d7bfcb0431 Stir to distribute seasonings.
9dae8112-7ae3-4c0e-a2c7-80d7bfcb0431 Cook another 2 to 3 minutes until asparagus is tender. Stir once more before serving.
9dae8112-7ae3-4c0e-a2c7-80d7bfcb0431 Serve and enjoy!
f8b72b96-a05c-4651-b9e6-44ec5441b04f Preheat oven to 425 F
f8b72b96-a05c-4651-b9e6-44ec5441b04f Brush a baking sheet with a little bit of oil or cover with parchment paper.
f8b72b96-a05c-4651-b9e6-44ec5441b04f Arrange the cabbage slices on a baking sheet. Brush one side with a light coating of olive oil. Lightly season with salt and pepper.
f8b72b96-a05c-4651-b9e6-44ec5441b04f Cook until the cabbage is tender in the middle and the edges are browned and crispy (about 40 minutes)
f8b72b96-a05c-4651-b9e6-44ec5441b04f In a food processor, pulse the walnuts, garlic, and cheese until finely chopped.
f8b72b96-a05c-4651-b9e6-44ec5441b04f Add the parsley. With the blade running, slowly pour in half the olive oil. Continue adding oil until the pesto has the consistency you want. (It’s not necessary to use all of the olive oil if the pesto reaches your desired consistency first.)
f8b72b96-a05c-4651-b9e6-44ec5441b04f Add salt to taste.
f8b72b96-a05c-4651-b9e6-44ec5441b04f Drizzle pesto over the cabbage. Serve warm or at room temperature.
0da88745-679f-4d67-87c1-6505e97078f4 Gather the ingredients.
0da88745-679f-4d67-87c1-6505e97078f4 Peel the banana and slice lengthwise.
0da88745-679f-4d67-87c1-6505e97078f4 Melt brown sugar and butter in a small saucepan.
0da88745-679f-4d67-87c1-6505e97078f4 Add the banana and sauté until tender.
0da88745-679f-4d67-87c1-6505e97078f4 Sprinkle with the ground cinnamon. Add the banana liqueur and rum. Gently warm the alcohol and coat the bananas in the sauce.
0da88745-679f-4d67-87c1-6505e97078f4 Ignite the sauce with a flame.
0da88745-679f-4d67-87c1-6505e97078f4 Baste the bananas in the liquid until the flame burns out.
0da88745-679f-4d67-87c1-6505e97078f4 Serve the bananas foster immediately with a scoop of ice cream, and enjoy.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f Gather the ingredients.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs and milk.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f In another large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, salt, and baking powder.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f Gradually combine the wet and dry ingredients. Beat until very smooth.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f Heat oil (at least 1 inch deep) in electric skillet to 375 degrees F. There are two different options stream the batter into the hot oil.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f Move the funnel or zip-top bag over the hot oil to make a pattern, starting at the center of the pan and swirling batter outward in a circle. Fry for 2 to 3 minutes, or until brown.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f Once the funnel cakes are browned on both sides, remove from the hot oil using a slotted spoon. Drain excess oil on a paper towel-lined plate.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f Transfer to a rack and dust with confectioners’ sugar.
dd2b073f-2e88-4d03-9db5-e7d14942ae7f Serve funnel cakes immediately. They can be enjoyed just with the powdered sugar, or with additional toppings like fruit sauce, hot fudge, whipped cream, or ice cream.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Gather the ingredients.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Heat the oven to 350 F. Strain an 8-ounce can of pineapple rings in a colander and reserve the liquid from the can. This flavorful juice will be used several times through the recipe to infuse pineapple flavor into every bite.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Pour melted butter into the bottom of a 9-inch cake pan and distribute evenly. In a small bowl, combine brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of the reserved pineapple juice. Sprinkle into the bottom of the cake pan and distribute evenly.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Arrange the pineapple rings in the pan on top of the brown sugar.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Fill the centers of each pineapple ring with maraschino cherries. Set aside while you make the batter.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Beat shortening, granulated sugar, and egg together until well-blended.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Combine the flour, baking powder, and salt.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Measure the remaining pineapple juice and add water as necessary to make 2/3 cup.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Add half of the flour mixture to the shortening mixture and beat to combine.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Add pineapple juice with vanilla and remaining dry mixture, beat to combine.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Pour over pineapple rings and place in oven. Bake until batter is done in the middle, about 45 minutes.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Cool 5 minutes before running a knife around the edge to loosen cake from pan.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Invert cake onto serving plate.
9fc1cf0f-1480-4f2c-a979-a1937f5a6a55 Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Gather the ingredients.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Preheat the oven to 325 F. Grease a 9x13 pan with non-stick cooking spray or softened butter and line with parchment.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Place the oil and butter in a large microwave-safe bowl and microwave on high in 30-second bursts until the butter melts.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Add the cocoa and espresso powders and whisk to combine. Add the sugars and whisk to combine. Add the eggs and vanilla, all at once, and whisk very gently until combined.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Sprinkle the flour and the salt over the batter and, using a rubber spatula, gently fold the dry into the wet until no visible flour remains.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Transfer the batter to the prepared pan, spread with an offset spatula, and sprinkle with the flaky sea salt, if using.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Bake for about 20 to 22 minutes, rotating the pan at the halfway point. The brownies are ready when a cake tester comes out with a few moist crumbs. Don't overbake.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Let the brownies cool on a rack until room temperature. If desired, freeze them briefly before cutting, as this makes for cleaner squares.
34ce9893-8a66-4435-8a6f-0311c2c8c5b2 Serve with glasses of cold whole milk.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f Gather the ingredients.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f Heat oven to 350 F. Butter a 9-by-13-inch baking pan. Mix the graham cracker crumbs and 1/3 cup of sugar. Stir in the melted butter. Pat into the bottom of prepared baking pan and set aside.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f Beat the 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f Pour over the graham cracker crust and smooth out evenly. Bake for 20 minutes. Set on wire rack to cool.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f Beat pumpkin, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, the milk, salt, and cinnamon in top of a double boiler. Cook over boiling water, stirring frequently until thick, about 5 minutes.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f In a small saucepan, sprinkle the gelatin in cold water. Stir over low heat just until dissolved.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f Stir the gelatin into the pumpkin mixture. Set aside to cool completely.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f When cooled, beat the egg whites in electric mixer until foamy. Gradually beat in the 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff and glossy.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f Pour over the cream cheese layer in pan and refrigerate until very cold and set, at least 3 hours.
ce07034c-0f01-4ca7-a7c0-8a2d5591996f To serve, cut into 15 squares. Each square can also be topped with sweetened whipped cream, if desired.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Gather the ingredients.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Sift flour and 3/4 cup of the sugar together 3 times.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar in large bowl on the highest speed of an electric mixer until it is light and fluffy. If you have no mixer, you can use a whisk but be prepared for a workout.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Sprinkle the remaining 3/4 cup of sugar over egg whites, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Fold in vanilla and almond extracts.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Sift dry ingredients, 2 tablespoons at a time, onto the beaten egg whites. Fold in gently but thoroughly with a wire whip or rubber spatula.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Pour batter into ungreased tube pan (10 x 4 inches). Make sure that there is not a trace of any fat or grease in pan, or cake won’t rise.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Draw a skewer gently through batter in a swirly pattern to remove large air bubbles.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Bake in preheated 350 F. oven for 40-50 minutes or until crust is golden brown and cracks are very dry.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 If your tube pan has legs (like the one seen here), invert and allow to cool at least one hour. If your tube pan does not have legs, invert the pan over a bottle to cool.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Once cooled, run a knife along the outside and carefully remove the cake from the pan. Place on a serving plate.
c52bf113-3416-48bf-8e32-961b805b48c3 Dust with powdered sugar and serve with fresh fruit.
b184b03e-677f-4012-a84e-a910b3ae4d8a Gather the ingredients. Top a baking sheet with waxed paper.
b184b03e-677f-4012-a84e-a910b3ae4d8a In a medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and evaporated milk. Warm over gentle heat until melted, stirring constantly.
b184b03e-677f-4012-a84e-a910b3ae4d8a Stir in the powdered sugar and sweetened flaked coconut.
b184b03e-677f-4012-a84e-a910b3ae4d8a Scoop 1-inch balls and place on the prepared baking sheet.
b184b03e-677f-4012-a84e-a910b3ae4d8a Press one whole almond into the top of each ball. Gently coax the dough into the signature oblong shape of an Almond Joy candy.
b184b03e-677f-4012-a84e-a910b3ae4d8a Chill for a couple of hours until firm. You know the cookies are set when they easily peel away from the waxed paper.
b184b03e-677f-4012-a84e-a910b3ae4d8a Gently peel the cookies away from the waxed paper to remove from baking sheet. Store between layers of waxed paper in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 Gather the ingredients.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. Prepare baking sheets by covering them with parchment paper.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 In a large bowl, cream together butter, granulated sugar, and light brown sugar until light and fluffy.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 Beat in the eggs and vanilla extract.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 In a separate medium bowl, combine the flour and salt.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 Gradually add the flour mixture to the creamed butter mixture.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 Mix in the macadamia nuts and white chocolate chips.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto the prepared baking sheet. Use an ice cream scoop to create uniform sized cookies, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 Bake for 15 minutes until the cookies are lightly golden and set. Allow to cool on a wire rack.
031dcf30-cfd2-4f11-be00-7236ac71cd86 Store cookies in airtight container.
fe1b5287-1866-4ac8-8308-d02803b74e5c Pre-heat the oven to 325 degrees F and butter and flour an 8" square baking pan.
fe1b5287-1866-4ac8-8308-d02803b74e5c Add the butter and chocolate to a heat-proof bowl and set it over a pot of simmering water. Stir until melted and allow to cool slightly.
fe1b5287-1866-4ac8-8308-d02803b74e5c Whisk the granulated sugar into the butter and chocolate mixture, then whisk in the eggs and vanilla.
fe1b5287-1866-4ac8-8308-d02803b74e5c Sift together the all-purpose flour, baking powder and salt and stir into the chocolate batter.
fe1b5287-1866-4ac8-8308-d02803b74e5c Make the peanut butter swirl filling by stirring together the melted butter, confectioners sugar, peanut butter and salt until smooth.
fe1b5287-1866-4ac8-8308-d02803b74e5c Pour the chocolate batter into the prepared pan and spread out evenly. Drop tablespoons of peanut butter filling on top of the batter and use a butter knife or a long skewer to gently swirl the peanut butter filling into the batter. Do not mix all the way so that the pretty swirl pattern remains on top.
fe1b5287-1866-4ac8-8308-d02803b74e5c Bake for about 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. Let cool and cut into 9 squares. Note that you can add a cup of chocolate chips or peanut butter chips to the batter before baking, if you like.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 Gather the ingredients.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 Heat oven to 375 degrees F and cover baking sheets with parchment paper.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 Stir in flour, 1 cup of the crushed potato chips, baking soda, and baking powder until dough forms.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place balls 2 inches apart on prepared baking sheets and press each ball to flatten slightly. You can use your fingers or the bottom of a glass to flatten.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are light golden brown. Cool 3 minutes; remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks. Cool completely.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 In small microwavable bowl, microwave chocolate chips and peanut butter chips uncovered on high for 1 minute to 1 minute 30 seconds, stirring every 30 seconds, until melted and smooth. The chips can also be melted gently in a double boiler over simmering water.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 Dip each cookie halfway into melted chocolate mixture, letting excess drip off.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 Immediately sprinkle the dipped half of each cookie with remaining crushed potato chips. Place on waxed paper until set, about 1 hour.
e44d2ab4-782d-4eb9-bc58-3b32ff9f9696 Store between sheets of waxed paper in tightly covered container.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Gather the ingredients.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Start by preparing the baking powder pastry. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Using a pastry blender or two knives in a criss-cross fashion, cut in the cold butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d In a separate small bowl, whisk together the milk and egg.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Gradually stir the egg mixture into flour mixture with fork until just combined and the dough cleans the side of bowl.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d On a lightly floured surface, lightly knead for about 1 minute to form a soft dough.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Divide dough in half and wrap each piece in plastic wrap. Refrigerate while you prepare the rest of the recipe.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d To make the apple pie filling, heat the apples and water, covered, in a medium saucepan to boiling, then reduce heat to low. All to simmer, covered, until apples soften slightly, about 5 minutes. Remove the cover and cook, stirring constantly until liquid evaporates, about 3 minutes.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Stir in the granulated sugar and butter. Cook, uncovered for 3 minutes and then stir in the cinnamon.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Mash the mixture with a fork or potato masher to form a chunky puree. Cover and refrigerate until cold, about 1 hour.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d When you are ready to prepare the pies, roll one half of dough 1/8-inch thick on floured surface. Cut out 4-to-5-inch circles with floured cutter. (If you don't have a cutter large enough, you can trace around the edge of an inverted bowl to form the circles.)
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Spread some of the apple mixture over half of each circle, leaving a 3/4-inch border.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Lightly brush borders with a little water. Fold the pastry in half and pinch the edges lightly with fingers. Seal the edges with a fork. Turn the pies over and again press the seams with a fork. (Do not pierce the dough). Repeat with the remaining dough and filling.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Heat oil in a large skillet to 375 degrees F. Fry the pies, 4 at a time so as to not crowd the pan. Turn the pies once, until they are golden brown on both sides, about 4 minutes.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Using a slotted spoon, lift the pies out of the oil and drain on to a paper towel lined plate.
8010daf6-e096-4892-a324-f75fe7857a9d Dust the pies with powdered sugar and serve immediately.
f2db96e7-93ef-4e9e-b11e-7bf99e190783 Place the chopped chocolate into a bowl and set over a pan of gently simmering water to melt. Take care not to let the bowl touch the water, or it will scorch. Or, melt the chocolate in the microwave a few seconds at a time as the chocolate can quickly burn if done too quickly. Once the chocolate is melted, remove from the heat.
f2db96e7-93ef-4e9e-b11e-7bf99e190783 Using an electric mixer if possible (this makes the job so much easier!), beat the sugar and butter together until light and fluffy and pale in color. If you don't have an electric mixer, then use a balloon whisk. Add the salt and mix, then add the vanilla extract and mix again.
f2db96e7-93ef-4e9e-b11e-7bf99e190783 With the mixer still running, slowly pour the melted chocolate into the butter and sugar mixture and continue to blend until thoroughly incorporated. Then, add the eggs one at a time, mixing each well after each one before adding another.
f2db96e7-93ef-4e9e-b11e-7bf99e190783 Pour the chocolate filling into the crust and smooth the surface with a spatula. Pop the pie into the fridge and leave for 3 to 4 hours, preferably overnight until entirely set.
f2db96e7-93ef-4e9e-b11e-7bf99e190783 Once set firmly, decorate with whipped cream and grated chocolate, shavings or curls. The pie can be made a day ahead of serving, but only decorate just before.
0dc76f01-4d26-446e-98af-8491f5fbe263 Gather the ingredients.
0dc76f01-4d26-446e-98af-8491f5fbe263 Place the strawberries in a bowl and mash with a wooden spoon. Set aside.
0dc76f01-4d26-446e-98af-8491f5fbe263 If desired, strain the mixture to remove the seeds.
0dc76f01-4d26-446e-98af-8491f5fbe263 Using a hand mixer or a stand mixer with the whisk attachment, whip the cream with sugar until it reaches soft peaks.
0dc76f01-4d26-446e-98af-8491f5fbe263 Add the mashed berries and continue whipping until the mixture forms stiff peaks and a traditional whipped cream texture develops.
0dc76f01-4d26-446e-98af-8491f5fbe263 Use the whipped cream immediately, as it may not retain its texture after a day or so in the refrigerator.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 In a food processor, combine the 1 cup of flour, the granulated sugar, baking powder, and salt. Pulse to combine thoroughly.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Cut 10 tablespoons of cold butter into small pieces. Gradually add the butter pieces to the flour mixture, pulsing briefly after each addition. Pulse just until many of the crumbs are about the size of peas. Drizzle the ice water into the food processor while pulsing.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 When the mixture begins to clump together, transfer it to a floured surface. Knead a few times to form a cohesive dough. Flatten the dough into a disk and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for at least 45 minutes.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Line a baking sheet with wax paper or parchment paper.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Remove the dough to a floured surface and roll it out into a large square about 1/4-inch in thickness. With a pizza cutter or knife, cut it into squares, rectangles, or other shapes. Place the dough pieces on the lined baking pan and place the pan in the freezer.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Peel a pear and slice in half lengthwise. With a melon baller, remove the core and cut out the stem and blossom end; remove any tough fibers. Place a pear half on a cutting board, cut-side down. Slice it into 1/4-inch wedges. Toss the wedges in a large bowl with the 1 tablespoon of lemon juice. Peel, core, and slice the remaining pears and add them to the bowl. Add the vanilla and toss to combine.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 In another bowl, combine the brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and the remaining 3 tablespoons of flour. Mix well. Sprinkle the brown sugar mixture over the pears while tossing to coat thoroughly.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Preheat the oven to 375 F.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Put the pears in a 10-inch cast iron skillet. Cut the remaining tablespoon of butter into small pieces and scatter them over the pear filling. Drizzle with syrup or molasses, if using.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Remove the dough pieces from the freezer and arrange them over the pear filling. Overlap them as needed.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Combine the egg white and water and whisk to make the egg wash. Brush the egg wash mixture lightly over the pieces of dough. Sprinkle with sanding sugar, if desired.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Bake in the preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes, or until the topping is golden brown and the pears are tender.
fea13686-5c5a-4d4b-b8bf-36cff782e821 Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 Gather the ingredients.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 Spray doughnut pans with nonstick cooking or baking spray.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 In a medium bowl, combine the flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt. Blend thoroughly with a whisk or spoon.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 In a large mixing bowl, whisk the eggs with the milk, melted butter, 2 teaspoons of orange zest and 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla extract.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 Add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture along with the finely chopped cranberries. Mix just until the ingredients are moistened.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 Spoon the batter into the cavities of the doughnut pans, filling about half full. Alternatively, spoon the batter into a plastic food storage bag, cut off a small piece of the corner and pipe the batter into the pan.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 Bake the doughnuts for about 10 to 12 minutes (about 7 to 9 minutes for mini doughnuts), or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into a doughnut.
ff031a12-dac8-4919-90b4-9e1e3434d128 Let the doughnuts cool for about 5 minutes and then carefully remove them to a rack to cool completely.
6785a9ef-620a-4759-a942-c109167cb9af Gather the ingredients.
6785a9ef-620a-4759-a942-c109167cb9af In a medium saucepan sift the cocoa powder, flour, sugar, and salt and whisk to combine.
6785a9ef-620a-4759-a942-c109167cb9af Slowly add milk and whisk until all the lumps are gone.
6785a9ef-620a-4759-a942-c109167cb9af Place the saucepan over medium heat and cook for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring constantly, until the gravy just begins to boil and then thickens.
6785a9ef-620a-4759-a942-c109167cb9af Once thick, remove from the heat and stir in butter and vanilla. Continue stirring until the butter has melted.
6785a9ef-620a-4759-a942-c109167cb9af Serve immediately, spooned over biscuits.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 Gather the ingredients.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and salt. Add shortening and cut into flour and salt with a pastry blender until coarse and crumbly.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 Stir in ice water, a little at a time until dough forms in a ball. Wrap dough in plastic wrap and chill for 20 minutes.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 Roll out dough into a circle and fit into a pie plate.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 Preheat charcoal or gas grill for indirect cooking at 400 F.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 In a small bowl, combine the granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, and cloves.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 In a separate large bowl, toss apple slices with lemon juice (to prevent the apples from turning brown). Then add the sugar/flour/spice mixture to the apples and toss to coat the apple slices with the spice mixture.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 In a medium bowl, combine the remaining 1/2 cup flour with the brown sugar. Add the pieces of butter, and cut in with a pastry blender, until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle evenly over the apples.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 Place the pie on a cookie sheet, and bake over indirect heat until the apples are tender and bubbly about 50 to 60 minutes. Remove the pie and let sit for at least 10 minutes to cool before serving.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 Serve with generous scoops of ice cream and slices of extra sharp Cheddar cheese.
e972832a-0ae7-47ba-9c3f-5e9a1e8cea47 Enjoy!
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Gather the ingredients.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Preheat oven to 350 F. Grease 9x13 pan.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Toss apple slices with spices and set aside.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, and salt with a wire whisk.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Add eggs one at a time.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Add flour mixture alternately with apple schnapps.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Stir in apple slices.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Transfer batter to greased pan.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Bake for 30 to 38 minutes.
504c7806-cb09-4d0c-9aad-fa089d182b6b Serve apple spice cake with a dollop of whipped cream and sprinkled with cinnamon.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 In a large bowl combine crushed vanilla wafer cookies, melted butter, and sugar. In this recipe, vanilla wafer cookies are crushed and used in the crust, while whole vanilla wafer cookies are also used as a garnish on top of the finished cheesecake. When you purchase an 11-ounce box of vanilla wafer cookies, first remove 12 cookies for the garnish. Then, pulse the remaining cookies in the box in the food processor. They will measure out to the 2 cups of cookie crumbs necessary for the crust.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 Pat the crust mixture into the bottom and halfway up the sides of a 10-inch springform pan. To prevent leaks, line the outside of the pan with aluminum foil or place the springform pan on a rimmed baking sheet.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, eggs, mashed bananas, and lemon juice until smooth.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and bake for 1 hour, or until the cheesecake is light brown on top.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 Cool completely at room temperature. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for at least 12 hours before serving.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 When ready to serve, prepare the topping. In a medium bowl, whisk together the milk, pudding mix, and powdered sugar. Beat for 2 minutes. Gently stir in the whipped topping.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 Spread the topping over the top of the cheesecake.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 Remove the side of the springform pan and place on serving platter. Garnish with vanilla wafer cookies and fresh banana slices.
d494cdf0-7c71-4a44-912c-cd501a22c5e3 Enjoy!
2ab0a1f8-67ca-41ad-83f7-086b32f4245d Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 325 F.
2ab0a1f8-67ca-41ad-83f7-086b32f4245d Thoroughly butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
2ab0a1f8-67ca-41ad-83f7-086b32f4245d Put the cake mix into a large bowl. Using a box grater, shred the cold butter into the dry ingredients. Toss to combine. If you don't have a box grater you can just cut the butter into small pieces with a pastry blender or mash it through the tines of a fork. Work quickly to avoid melting the butter.
2ab0a1f8-67ca-41ad-83f7-086b32f4245d Add the blueberries to the butter and flour mixture and toss to distribute the blueberries. Dump into the pan.
2ab0a1f8-67ca-41ad-83f7-086b32f4245d Add the buttermilk and vanilla to a measuring cup with a spout. Stir to combine.
2ab0a1f8-67ca-41ad-83f7-086b32f4245d Pour the buttermilk mixture evenly over the dry mixture in the baking pan. Do not mix. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until the cake is golden brown and the blueberries are bubbling. Remove from oven.
2ab0a1f8-67ca-41ad-83f7-086b32f4245d While the dump cake is cooling, prepare the whipped cream. In a large bowl, or in the bowl of a stand mixer, whisk the whipping cream and confectioners sugar until past the soft peak stage, but not quite stiff.
2ab0a1f8-67ca-41ad-83f7-086b32f4245d Serve the warm dump cake with a generous helping of whipped cream.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Gather the ingredients. Grease a 9-inch springform pan with cooking spray or softened butter. Line the bottom and sides with parchment paper.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a To make the crust, place 36 Oreos in a food processor fitted with the metal blade and process until fine crumbs form.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Add the melted butter and process until combined, scraping the bowl periodically with a rubber spatula.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Transfer the crumbs to the prepared pan and firmly press the crumbs into the bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of the pan. Place the crust in the freezer while you prepare the filling.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Place the heavy cream and vanilla in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the whisk attachment and whisk on medium-high until stiff peaks form. Transfer to a large bowl.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Place the cream cheese, sugar and salt in the bowl of the stand mixer, now fitted with the paddle attachment (no need to clean it) and beat on medium until smooth, scraping the bowl with a rubber spatula as needed.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Fold the whipped cream into the cream cheese in several installments with a rubber spatula, being mindful not to deflate the air you just whipped into the cream.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Process the remaining Oreos until coarse crumbs form. Gently fold the coarse crumbs into the cheesecake batter.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Transfer the filling to the prepared crust, smoothing the top with an offset spatula or butter knife. Add filling just to the top of the crust. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 5 hours, preferably overnight.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a When ready to serve, remove the sides of the pan and then slide a long knife between the parchment paper and the metal bottom to loosen and remove the sides. Peel off the parchment. Sprinkle crushed Oreos over the top of the cake to decorate.
d77edb2d-7a23-4780-bca6-b767066d732a Place the cake on a serving plate, slice into wedges with a serrated knife, and serve. Run the knife under hot water each time you make a cut to ensure clean slices.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb Gather the ingredients. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb To make the bread pudding, combine the heavy whipping cream, whole milk, and sugar in a medium heavy saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a simmer, stirring until the sugar dissolves.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb Remove the pan from the heat. Add the white chocolate chips and whisk until melted and smooth.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb In a large bowl, whisk the egg yolks and whole eggs.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb Slowly whisk in the warm cream and chocolate mixture into the egg mixture.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb Cut the challah bread into 1-inch cubes.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb Pour the white chocolate mixture over the cubed bread and stir until coated. Let stand for about 5 minutes, until the bread is soft.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb Transfer the bread mixture to the prepared dish.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb Cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 45 minutes. Remove the foil and bake for about 15 minutes until the pudding is golden brown and set. Cool slightly on a rack.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb When ready to serve, make the white chocolate sauce. In a small, heavy saucepan bring the heavy cream to a boil. Remove the pan from the heat. Add the white chocolate chips and whisk until melted and the sauce is smooth.
35fa1eec-d72b-44eb-8af7-05928e4332bb Serve the warm white chocolate bread pudding with a drizzle of the warm white chocolate sauce.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Gather the ingredients. Position an oven rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 350 F.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Unroll one can of the refrigerated crescent roll dough. Place in the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Stretch the dough to cover the bottom of the baking dish. Press the perforations to seal.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d In medium bowl, beat the softened cream cheese with 1 cup of the sugar, until smooth.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Beat in the egg and vanilla extract.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Gently spread the cream cheese mixture over the dough in the baking dish.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Unroll the second can of dough. Before placing it in the baking dish, press the perforations to seal. Carefully place the layer of dough on top of the cream cheese layer and gently stretch as needed to cover. Pinch seams together, sealing the top and bottom crescent roll layers together.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Pour the melted butter evenly over the top of the dough.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar with the cinnamon, and sprinkle evenly over butter.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Bake 30-35 minutes until the dough is golden brown and the cinnamon-sugar has formed a crust on top of the dough. Cool for 15-20 minutes before cutting into squares to serve.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Drizzle each bar with desired amount of honey.
8b83b904-979b-460d-9438-8c2d6dd5547d Cover and refrigerate any remaining bars for up to one week.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F. Grease an 8 x 8-inch square baking pan and set aside.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd In a separate bowl, combine the sugar, melted butter, eggs, and vanilla extract.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd Stir the flour mixture into the butter mixture.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd Divide the batter evenly into two separate bowls.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd In one bowl, stir in the unsweetened cocoa powder. In the other bowl, stir in the pumpkin puree and pumpkin pie spice.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd Spread half of the chocolate brownie batter into the bottom of the prepared baking pan.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd Gently spread half of the spiced pumpkin batter on top of the chocolate layer.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd Spoon dollops of the remaining chocolate and pumpkin batters on top of the pumpkin layer.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd Drag a kitchen knife back and forth through the batter dollops to create a swirl. Bake for about 45 minutes or until set.
597fda7c-39df-4885-8f3e-47602513cedd Cool on a wire rack and then cut into squares to serve. ﻿Enjoy!
fce94b9b-b071-43c8-b481-12fa7acf7c73 Gather the ingredients. Place a 12-ounce serving glass in the freezer to chill. You want the glass to be ice cold before making and serving an egg cream.
fce94b9b-b071-43c8-b481-12fa7acf7c73 Pour the cold milk into the chilled glass.
fce94b9b-b071-43c8-b481-12fa7acf7c73 Pour the seltzer into the glass until the white head reaches the top of the glass.
fce94b9b-b071-43c8-b481-12fa7acf7c73 Spoon the syrup into the glass and stir to combine. Serve with a straw.
97816915-d31c-4b55-ad73-b4ad6ba2132d Gather your ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
97816915-d31c-4b55-ad73-b4ad6ba2132d Add the sugar and eggs to a large mixing bowl and whisk to combine. Whisk until the eggs are completely incorporated into the sugar.
97816915-d31c-4b55-ad73-b4ad6ba2132d Add the evaporated milk, coconut cream, and vanilla to the sugar mixture. Then whisk in the melted butter.
97816915-d31c-4b55-ad73-b4ad6ba2132d Whisk in the rice flour, baking powder, and salt to the batter. Fold in the shredded coconut.
97816915-d31c-4b55-ad73-b4ad6ba2132d Line a 9 by 13-inch baking pan with parchment paper. Leave enough paper around the edges so you can use them to lift the cake out of the pan. You can also butter the pan or grease it with non-stick cooking spray.
97816915-d31c-4b55-ad73-b4ad6ba2132d Bake for about an hour. The baking time will vary based on your oven and climate. It will be golden brown on top and when you insert the toothpick in the middle it will come out mostly clean.
97816915-d31c-4b55-ad73-b4ad6ba2132d Allow the cake to cool. Then remove it using the edges of the parchment paper. Cut it into squares and serve. Top with more shredded coconut if you wish.
6933bb34-2444-40d6-aa4e-6e5bb704d441 Gather the ingredients and preheat the oven to 350 F.
6933bb34-2444-40d6-aa4e-6e5bb704d441 In a medium sized bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, soda, and salt.
6933bb34-2444-40d6-aa4e-6e5bb704d441 Add the water, vanilla, vinegar, and oil and whisk until fully incorporated and smooth.
6933bb34-2444-40d6-aa4e-6e5bb704d441 Transfer to a 9-inch pie plate and bake for 25 to 35 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out with a moist crumb or two.
6933bb34-2444-40d6-aa4e-6e5bb704d441 Make the frosting while the cake bakes and cools. Place the butter in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment and beat the butter on medium speed until soft and smooth.
6933bb34-2444-40d6-aa4e-6e5bb704d441 Add the sugar 1 cup at a time to the butter, mixing to combine on low, and alternating with the cream.
6933bb34-2444-40d6-aa4e-6e5bb704d441 Add the salt and vanilla and mix for about 5 minutes on medium until smooth, fluffy and spreadable.
6933bb34-2444-40d6-aa4e-6e5bb704d441 Generously frost the cake, decorate with rainbow sprinkles, and serve.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Gather the ingredients.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Preheat the oven to 350 F and grease three 8-inch pans with cooking spray or softened butter. Line the bottoms with parchment paper.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 To make the cake, combine the sugar, oil and vanilla in a large mixing bowl and whisk vigorously to combine.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Add the eggs and the yolks, one at a time, whisking after each addition to incorporate.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Add the milk and whisk a final time.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt and with a flexible spatula, gently fold the dry into the wet in 3 additions. The batter will be lumpy, but it is forgiving, and you can give it a quick whisk before filling the cake pans.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Pour a scant 2/3 of a cup of batter into each cake pan and bake for about 10 minutes, rotating at the halfway point. The cake layers are ready when a toothpick comes out with a moist crumb or two.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Let cool until the pans are easy to handle and then invert the layers onto cooling racks and repeat twice more with the remaining batter, cleaning, greasing and papering the pans between each round. When you are done, you should have 8 to 9 layers total.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Make the frosting while the layers bake. In a medium saucepan over medium heat, combine the sugar and evaporated milk and cook until the sugar melts.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Add the chocolates and butter, increase the heat to medium high, and cook until melted.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Once melted, reduce the heat back to medium and stir occasionally until the mixture thickens, about 10 to 15 minutes. It should resemble hot fudge sauce.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Add the vanilla and salt, stir and transfer to a different vessel (to help it come to room temperature more quickly) and set aside to cool and thicken. You may place it in the refrigerator, stirring frequently, to speed up this process.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 To frost the cake, place a layer on a cake stand and spread a quarter cup of frosting over the layer.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Place another layer on top and repeat. Continue layering and frosting until you run out of layers.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Spread the frosting on the top of the cake and on the sides. Let the frosting set up for about 30 minutes before serving.
9714b659-7a63-465d-b74b-48a3a24e5824 Decorate with sanding sugar or sprinkles if you wish.
781854a9-1666-44b6-bc42-09580899f3d5 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 375 F. Prepare baking sheets by lining with parchment paper.
781854a9-1666-44b6-bc42-09580899f3d5 In a large bowl, combine the flour and baking soda. Set aside.
781854a9-1666-44b6-bc42-09580899f3d5 In a large mixer bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar, instant vanilla pudding mix, and vanilla. Beat until smooth and creamy.
781854a9-1666-44b6-bc42-09580899f3d5 Beat in the eggs until well combined.
781854a9-1666-44b6-bc42-09580899f3d5 Gradually add the flour mixture to the butter mixture.
781854a9-1666-44b6-bc42-09580899f3d5 Stir in the chocolate chips.
781854a9-1666-44b6-bc42-09580899f3d5 Drop by heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets. Bake in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
781854a9-1666-44b6-bc42-09580899f3d5 Cool on a wire rack. Store in an airtight container if not eating right away.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Gather the ingredients.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Combine the oil and sugar in a 12-ounce microwave safe mug and use a fork to combine.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Add the yolk and vanilla and mix again.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Add the heavy cream and mix again.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Add the peanut butter and mix a final time.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Add the flour, baking powder, and salt to the mug and again, using the fork, mix to combine.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Add the chocolate chips and mix again.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Place the mug in the microwave and microwave on high for about 1 1/2 minutes. The cake is done when its top has risen and is lightly sticky, but not wet. The cake will sink as it cools. do not be alarmed.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 Serve warm with a dollop of whipped cream or a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
9fa0e77e-fd47-4fbc-8c3b-3895ee0e2230 RECIPE VARIATIONS:
75c361df-fee4-4571-bb13-2e49ddac1a0e Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line two baking sheets with parchment paper.
75c361df-fee4-4571-bb13-2e49ddac1a0e Place the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a medium bowl and whisk to combine.
75c361df-fee4-4571-bb13-2e49ddac1a0e In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, cream the butter, sugar, and vanilla on medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping down the bowl with a rubber spatula as needed.
75c361df-fee4-4571-bb13-2e49ddac1a0e Add the egg and cream and mix on low speed for one minute, scraping down the bowl as needed. The mixture will look curdled.
75c361df-fee4-4571-bb13-2e49ddac1a0e Add the flour mixture all at once and mix just to incorporate.
75c361df-fee4-4571-bb13-2e49ddac1a0e Using a teaspoon-sized measuring spoon, portion the dough, roll into balls, and place on the prepared sheets. Use the heel of your hand to slightly flatten each ball. Place the pans in the freezer for 15 minutes.
75c361df-fee4-4571-bb13-2e49ddac1a0e Bake for 15 to 18 minutes, rotating the pans at the halfway point, until golden brown.
75c361df-fee4-4571-bb13-2e49ddac1a0e Place the pans on cooling racks and let the wafers come to room temperature before serving.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 Gather the ingredients.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 In a medium sized bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda and powder, and salt.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 In the bowl of a stand mixer, fitted with the paddle attachment, combine the butter, shortening, the sugars, and vanilla, and mix on medium until incorporated, about two minutes.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 Add the eggs and yolk all at once, and mix on low until incorporated, scraping down the bowl as needed with a rubber spatula. Add the peanut butter, and mix on medium until smooth and uniform, scraping the bowl as needed.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 Add the dry ingredients all at once and mix on low just until combined. Place the mixing bowl in the refrigerator for about an hour, or until the dough is firm enough to roll into balls.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 Preheat the oven to 350 F and line a cookie sheet with parchment paper.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 Bake cookies for 10 minutes, rotating the pan at the halfway point. The cookies will be just lightly browned and starting to crack slightly when they are done. Immediately upon removing the sheet from the oven, gently place a chocolate kiss in the center of each cookie.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 Immediately upon removing the sheet from the oven, gently place a chocolate kiss in the center of each cookie.
cb8d1d68-7158-40f9-bc09-2e2ad6eefed9 Repeat with the remaining balls of cookie dough, being careful to keep extra dough chilled between batches.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f Gather the ingredients. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flours, 1/3 cup of the sugar, yeast, potato starch (if using), and salt.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, beat the eggs on medium-high speed until light and frothy, about 3 minutes. Add the butter and evaporated milk and beat on medium to combine.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f Replace the paddle attachment with the dough hook, and on low speed, add the flour mixture and mix for about 5 minutes until the dough is smooth and slightly sticky.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f Turn the dough out into a medium bowl that has been greased with cooking spray or softened butter. Turn the dough ball over in the bowl to coat it in spray or butter, cover the bowl with plastic wrap, and set aside to rise for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until it has practically doubled in size.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f Remove the dough from the bowl, place it on your work surface (you should not need to flour it, but do so lightly, if the dough is too sticky to work with) and pat the dough or roll it out into a 10 x 12-inch square, about 1/2-inch thick.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f With a 3-inch cookie cutter, cut out the doughnuts and place on the prepared sheet. You may re-roll your scraps and cut out additional doughnuts, but they will be tougher than your first 12.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f Place the baking sheet in a warm spot, lightly covered in plastic wrap, and let the doughnuts rest on the counter until they have doubled in size, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f When ready to fry, fill a large, heavy pot with 2 inches of oil. Attach a candy thermometer to the side of the pot and heat the oil on medium-high heat until the temperature reaches 350 F, or slightly above (the temperature will drop when you add your doughnuts, but while frying, you want your temperature to stay at 350 F).
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f Once the oil is at temperature, carefully transfer a couple of doughnuts to the oil and fry for about 90 seconds per side, or until lightly browned. Repeat with the remaining doughnuts, being careful not to overcrowd the pan and lower the temperature of the oil too much.
ad8030b0-a5d1-429c-9c85-5ecc0edd5e9f Without burning your fingers, dip the warm doughnuts into the remaining sugar and flip to coat. Serve immediately. The doughnuts will keep for a day or two, but they are best eaten within a few hours of making.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 450 F.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 In a large mixing bowl, beat the egg yolks. Set aside.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 In another large bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff. Slowly mix in the sugar until stiff peaks form.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 Fold the beaten whites into the beaten yolks.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 In a medium bowl, combine the flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, and salt.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 Alternately add the flour mixture with the sour cream to the egg mixture.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 In a medium bowl, combine the butter and vinegar. Stir in the walnuts and raisins.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 Add the nut mixture to the egg and flour mixture.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 Pour the mixture into the prepared pie shell. Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes. Then reduce heat to 400 F and bake 5 minutes more. Finally, reduce the heat to 350 F and bake until the filling begins to set, about 15 minutes more.
4f45629b-46a0-4cb5-888a-5b2e14a0cd58 Cool completely. Top with whipped cream to serve.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Preheat oven to 350 F.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Whisk together flour, baking soda, and salt in a bowl and set aside.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 In a different bowl, beat softened butter, sugar, and brown sugar until creamy.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Add vanilla extract and egg, and beat until mixed well.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Combine the flour mixture with the wet mixture and mix well until all of the flour is incorporated.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Add the chocolate chips. Mix.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Grease a skillet and add half of the cookie dough. Press it into the pan.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Spread peanut butter generously over the dough. Then carefully top with the other half of the cookie dough. Be sure to work the dough so it completely covers and encases the peanut butter.
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until the edges are golden brown
de87ae0c-f7a3-4aa3-ab46-0b77ef61f8f7 Cut and serve with ice cream and whipped cream if you like. ​
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 Gather the ingredients.
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 Set a large baking sheet on a sturdy counter or tabletop and sprinkle it lightly with water.
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 Combine the sugar, water, and corn syrup in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Stir until the sugar dissolves, then cover the pan and allow the sugar syrup to boil for 2 to 3 minutes. Remove the lid, and continue to cook the syrup, without stirring, until it reaches 240 F (115 C).
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 Pour the sugar syrup onto the prepared baking sheet. Allow it to sit at room temperature for several minutes. After 2 to 3 minutes, lightly touch the syrup with a fingertip. When it is warm, but not hot, you can work with it.
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 Dampen a metal spatula or dough scraper with water, and use the scraper to push the syrup into a pile in the middle of the sheet.
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 Using a dampened plastic spatula or wooden spoon, begin to “cream,” or work, the fondant in a figure 8 pattern.
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 Continually scrape the fondant into the center, draw a figure 8, then scrape it together again. At first, the fondant will be very clear and fluid, but it will gradually become more opaque and creamy. After 5 to 10 minutes, the fondant will become very stiff, crumbly, and hard to manipulate.
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 Once the fondant reaches this state, moisten your hands and begin kneading it into a ball like bread dough. It will come together and will become softer and smoother. Stop kneading once your fondant is smooth, with no lumps.
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 At this point, your fondant can be used for melting and pouring. Once the fondant is melted and smooth, pour it into your desired receptacle such as small candy cups and topped with other candies or nuts. Once the poured fondant hardens, it can be served as is, as the paper cups easily peel away. If it is difficult to pour the fondant from the saucepan, pour it into a measuring cup with a spout.
33ba2102-a8a3-4c94-b6b3-5e3441c07651 If you want to make flavored fondant candies, it is best to “ripen” your fondant for at least 12 hours to obtain the best flavor and texture. To ripen the fondant, place it in an airtight plastic container, press plastic wrap directly onto the surface of the fondant, and seal the lid on tightly. Ripen the fondant at room temperature, or if it is hot, in the refrigerator. After ripening, the fondant can be flavored, rolled, and shaped in whatever manner you wish. If it is stiff, you can always knead it by hand on a surface dusted with powdered sugar, until it is easy to manage.
6d13f348-008d-49e6-a399-38cead3b40b7 Gather the ingredients.
6d13f348-008d-49e6-a399-38cead3b40b7 Coarsely chop up the almond paste into quarter-size chunks, then place the almond paste in the bowl of a large stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment.
6d13f348-008d-49e6-a399-38cead3b40b7 Add powdered sugar to the bowl and mix on low speed until the mixture has a fine, sandy texture. If you don't have a stand mixer, feel free to use a food processor.
6d13f348-008d-49e6-a399-38cead3b40b7 Pulse the almond paste and powdered sugar until the mixture resembles wet sand.
6d13f348-008d-49e6-a399-38cead3b40b7 With the mixer on low, slowly add the egg whites (and almond extract, if using) until the mixture pulls away from the sides of the bowl and forms a ball. If you are using a food processor, you'll notice a similar change. You may not need to add all of the egg whites.
6d13f348-008d-49e6-a399-38cead3b40b7 Dust a countertop with powdered sugar and knead the marzipan until it develops a smooth, pliable texture. It should have no lumps or dry patches.
6d13f348-008d-49e6-a399-38cead3b40b7 Use the marzipan immediately or store it for later use. To store your marzipan, cover it tightly in plastic wrap, then seal it in a plastic bag. Not only will your marzipan stay moist, but it also won't absorb any unfortunate odors or tastes. Marzipan will keep for three months in the refrigerator or up to six months in the freezer. Make sure to bring marzipan to room temperature before using it.
6d13f348-008d-49e6-a399-38cead3b40b7 Enjoy it on your favorite cake or as a tasty, nutty snack.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Gather the ingredients.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Place the white chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave it gently until melted, stirring after every 30 seconds to prevent overheating.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Place the strawberries in a small saucepan and heat them until they release their juices and become a chunky strawberry sauce. Blend them in a food processor or blender and then strain this mixture to remove any seeds. You will need 1/3 cup of strawberry puree for this recipe. If you have extra, save it for another purpose.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Combine the 1/3 cup of puree, the corn syrup, and the heavy cream in a saucepan over medium-high heat and heat, stirring, until the mixture comes to a boil.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Pour the hot puree over the melted chocolate and whisk until combined.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Stir in the citric acid and the lemon zest, and a drop or two of red food coloring, if using. This is your ganache. Cover the top of the ganache with cling wrap and refrigerate it until the mixture is firm enough to scoop and roll (about 2 hours).
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c If you are using the candied lemon zest and/or freeze-dried strawberries for decoration, prepare those while you wait.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Chop the candied zest into small strips, and place the freeze-dried strawberries in a food processor and process until they are a fine powder.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Melt the white chocolate candy coating in the microwave, stirring after every 30 seconds to prevent overheating.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Dust your hands with powdered sugar and roll the ganache into small balls between your palms, re-applying powdered sugar whenever it starts to get sticky.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Using dipping tools or a fork, dip a truffle in the white chocolate coating, tap the fork against the sides of the bowl to remove excess chocolate and place the truffle on a foil-lined baking sheet. If you’re using the optional decorations, sprinkle the top of the truffle with candied lemon zest and strawberry powder while the chocolate is still wet. Repeat until all of the truffles have been dipped.
78fe8d8b-96b5-4e8a-9ec3-d4a08db36d0c Enjoy!
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Gather the ingredients. Prepare a 9 x 9-inch pan by lining it with aluminum foil and spraying the foil with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Place the granulated sugar, 1 1/2 cups of the water, and lemon juice in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Stir until the sugar dissolves and bring the mixture to a boil.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Brush down the sides of the pan with a wet pastry brush to prevent sugar crystals from forming and insert a candy thermometer to keep track of the temperature.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Allow the sugar mixture to continue boiling, without stirring, until it reaches 240 F on the candy thermometer. This process can take from 45 minutes to an hour. When the sugar syrup is around 225 F, gather the rest of the candy ingredients.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Place the remaining 3 cups of water in another, slightly larger saucepan. Add the cornstarch and cream of tartar and whisk until the starch dissolves and there are no lumps.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Place the saucepan over medium heat and bring the mixture to a boil, stirring or whisking constantly. The mixture will become thick and pasty.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Once the sugar syrup is at 240 F, remove it from the heat. Slowly and carefully pour it into the cornstarch mixture, whisking until it is fully incorporated.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Reduce the heat to low and simmer, whisking it every 8 to 10 minutes, for about an hour, until the candy has turned a light golden yellow color and is very thick and gluey.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Remove the pan from the heat and stir the rosewater and the food coloring into the preparation.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad Pour the candy into the prepared pan and allow it to set uncovered overnight.
7ed48f0f-7237-4e98-b0bf-56c91404cfad The next day, remove the candy from the pan using the foil as handles. Dust a clean and nonporous work station with powdered sugar and flip the candy onto it. Carefully peel off the foil from the back and dust the top with more sugar. Use an oiled and sharp chef’s knife to cut the Turkish delight into small squares. Dust each side of the square with powdered sugar to prevent stickiness.
